And you must all be his friends, which makes you my friends.

249
00:12:25,940 --> 00:12:26,940
So let's go.

250
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:28,690
Arms in the air, you're all getting hugs.

251
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:29,900
Hey, okay.

252
00:12:30,070 --> 00:12:32,480
I thought you said your father left you.

253
00:12:32,650 --> 00:12:34,780
He did. This is my stepfather.

254
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:36,450
You'll want him to leave. Just wait.

255
00:12:36,570 --> 00:12:38,490
Hello. Where's my Gracie?

256
00:12:38,660 --> 00:12:40,490
- Hey. - Victor.

257
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:42,040
How are you?

258
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,250
You know, ever since Blue was born,

259
00:12:43,330 --> 00:12:46,920
I kind of miss you being as big as a house with more of you to hug.

260
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,040
Yep.

261
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:50,670
And now, I've saved the biggest hug for last.

262
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,960
- Boundaries, please. Boundaries. - Let's show them how it's done.

263
00:12:53,130 --> 00:12:54,590
Unhand me.

264
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:57,260
I don't like this at all.

265
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,970
Thank you.

266
00:12:59,550 --> 00:13:01,810
There's nothing like the embrace of two proud Doyle men.

267
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:03,180
I am not a Doyle man.

268
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:04,350
Little Paddy Doyle.

269
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,810
- Winslow. - Okay, compromise. Winslow.

270
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:08,690
Hyphen-Doyle.

271
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:13,530
Hey, isn't he the guy from the Korndog commercials on TV?

272
00:13:13,610 --> 00:13:15,690
- Hey, you're right. - Well, you got me.

273
00:13:15,860 --> 00:13:17,110
- Korndog King. - No, no, no.

274
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,160
- One moment. - Please not this.

275
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:20,700
Now, in honour of Blue's birthday,

276
00:13:20,910 --> 00:13:23,410
I'm going to present each and every one of you with a free Korndog...

277
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,040
- Thank you. - ...on the house.

278
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,040
Teriaki dog.

279
00:13:27,210 --> 00:13:28,500
That's for you.

280
00:13:28,670 --> 00:13:30,330
Do these have any peanuts?

281
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:33,000
I would never put peanuts in a Korndog.

282
00:13:33,170 --> 00:13:34,170
Great.

283
00:13:34,340 --> 00:13:35,670
Go ahead, big guy, it's okay.

284
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:38,680
For the simple reason, you see, we deep-fry them in peanut oil.

285
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:39,800
Peanut oil?

286
00:13:39,890 --> 00:13:42,600
- What? - Johnny, spit it... Spit it out right away!

287
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:44,220
Okay, I got the phone, okay.

288
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:47,730
Spit it out, Johnny! Spit it out right away! Into Mama's hands.

289
00:13:47,850 --> 00:13:48,890
Deep breath for the EpiPen.

290
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:51,230
- It's okay. - What's happening to that kid's lips?

291
00:13:55,570 --> 00:13:58,030
- Azrael, bring me my plan. - Father?

292
00:13:58,110 --> 00:14:00,160
It's in the bathroom. Check my side of the sink.

293
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:01,240
Father?

294
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:02,950
It's feeding time.

295
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:04,830
Hackus dizzy.

296
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:07,000
Yes, I almost forgot.

297
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:09,420
Apparently, I have to keep you alive.

298
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:13,840
I hope you both appreciate what a tremendous burden this is upon me.

299
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,130
All right, mind your manners.

300
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,550
Thank you.

301
00:14:16,630 --> 00:14:20,840
If you were real Smurfs, I'd be taking essence from you.

302
00:14:21,930 --> 00:14:24,510
I didn't hear a "thank you."

303
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:26,310
Close enough. Come, come.

304
00:14:26,470 --> 00:14:30,600
We must review my plan before tonight's raid on Smurf Village.

305
00:14:32,690 --> 00:14:35,730
This is not my writing parchment. Where is my plan?

306
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:37,730
"Gone digital"?

307
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:39,950
I don't understand what that means.

308
00:14:40,030 --> 00:14:43,450
Yes, phase one, "Create Naughties." Yes.

309
00:14:43,620 --> 00:14:45,620
Check. Where is phase two?

310
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,960
I am enamoured of that swiping motion.

311
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,710
Yes, get away, get away, get away, get away.

312
00:14:54,790 --> 00:14:57,750
Phase three... Swipe.

313
00:14:57,920 --> 00:14:59,720
I capture my ungrateful daughter

314
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:04,010
and force her to tell me the secret formula that Papa used to turn her blue.

315
00:15:04,090 --> 00:15:05,180
Swipe.

316
00:15:05,350 --> 00:15:07,390
I turn you and hundreds other like you blue.

317
00:15:07,470 --> 00:15:08,470
Hackus blue!

318
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:10,480
Hackus blue!

319
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:14,400
I place you into a terrifying machine and extract your essence.

320
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:15,520
- What? - And then,

321
00:15:15,650 --> 00:15:19,610
the entire world shall bow before me!

322
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:23,610
Will that extracting thing hurt?

323
00:15:23,780 --> 00:15:26,280
It's excruciatingly painless.

324
00:15:26,370 --> 00:15:28,490
You'll see, it'll be fun, for me.

325
00:15:28,990 --> 00:15:30,580
Anyway, we're getting ahead of ourselves.

326
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:36,080
Back to phase two, the very reason we came to this cheese-infested metropolis.

327
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:39,590
The great iron spire.

328
00:15:39,670 --> 00:15:41,260
The only possible way

329
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:45,840
to harness enough energy to create a portal right into the heart of Smurf Village.

330
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:48,600
How I love portal creation.

331
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:51,770
Come, come, let us away! To the iron spire!

332
00:16:33,850 --> 00:16:35,940
It worked!

333
00:16:36,140 --> 00:16:38,560
Yes! Just enough essence!

334
00:16:47,070 --> 00:16:50,660
And now I will go down in history!

335
00:16:50,740 --> 00:16:53,620
Nothing can stop me now!

336
00:16:58,330 --> 00:17:00,420
My Gargaberries!

337
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,800
Oh, no!

338
00:17:06,340 --> 00:17:09,140
Now I shall prove my genius!

339
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:14,220
Head spin!

340
00:17:19,060 --> 00:17:24,280
It appears I lack sufficient essence to create a human-size portal.

341
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:27,570
Father, I can fit through there. Let me get Smurfette.

342
00:17:27,650 --> 00:17:28,700
Hackus go! Hackus go!

343
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:30,200
- Hey! - Hackus go!

344
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:33,240
Yes, yes. Well, let's see here.

345
00:17:33,990 --> 00:17:37,040
- Eeny, meeny, miny... - Pick me! Pick me!

346
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:38,170
Moron.

347
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:39,210
Yes!

348
00:17:39,290 --> 00:17:42,340
- Hey, Hackus, listen to this. - What?

349
00:17:42,420 --> 00:17:43,630
I win.

350
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:45,380
Nicely played, Vexy.

351
00:17:45,460 --> 00:17:47,050
Now, I must warn you.

352
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:49,720
Your destination is a true horror.

353
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:54,310
A realm filled with the relentless crushing quiet of peace,

354
00:17:54,390 --> 00:17:57,600
punctuated by the wretched cacophony of joyousness.

355
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:59,440
- It's horrible. - What a nightmare.

356
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:01,900
Yes, yes, it completely ruined your sister.

357
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:04,270
It's such a shame when a bad girl turns good.

358
00:18:04,360 --> 00:18:05,360
So true.

359
00:18:05,530 --> 00:18:08,990
But she does know the secret formula,

360
00:18:09,150 --> 00:18:12,320
so go get Smurfette!

361
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,080
I just don't get it.

362
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:22,290
They know how tough my birthday can be,

363
00:18:22,420 --> 00:18:25,250
and they didn't even remember.

364
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:28,170
Maybe Papa was wrong.

365
00:18:28,260 --> 00:18:31,180
Guess I'll never really be one of them.

366
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:38,680
- Oh, no! - Help.

367
00:18:38,850 --> 00:18:41,440
Please, wait.

368
00:18:42,690 --> 00:18:44,020
I escaped.

369
00:18:44,230 --> 00:18:45,360
Escaped?

370
00:18:45,940 --> 00:18:48,900
From the evil wizard who made me.

371
00:18:49,110 --> 00:18:52,110
Do you mean Gargamel?

372
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,780
Is Gargamel your father?

373
00:18:54,870 --> 00:18:56,330
Yes.

374
00:18:56,490 --> 00:18:59,040
But he's...

375
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:01,920
That means you're just like me.

376
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:04,170
- Gotcha! - What are you doing?

377
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:06,210
Father's going to be very happy.

378
00:19:06,460 --> 00:19:07,960
Smurfette's in trouble!

379
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:09,170
- Crikey! - Oh, no!

380
00:19:09,260 --> 00:19:11,300
- Come on, Smurfs! - Smurfette!

381
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:12,970
No!

382
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:15,800
- Oh, no, you don't. - No!

383
00:19:15,970 --> 00:19:17,390
- Let go! - Now get in there!

384
00:19:17,470 --> 00:19:19,020
Oh, no!

385
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:22,230
- She's being smurf napped. - Unhand her!

386
00:19:22,390 --> 00:19:25,020
So long, Smurfs.

387
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,150
- Smurfette! - Smurfette!

388
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:28,360
What are we gonna do now?

389
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:33,280
My powers of deduction lead me to believe that this is the work of Gargamel.

390
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:39,410
Oh, no, oh, no!

391
00:19:40,870 --> 00:19:43,080
- Yes! - Pretty blue.

392
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,500
Gargamel.

393
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:48,710
Smurfette. Welcome home.

394
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:57,510
You're wasting your time, Gargamel.

395
00:19:57,600 --> 00:19:59,310
Papa and the others are gonna come for me.

396
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:02,230
I don't think so.

397
00:20:02,310 --> 00:20:03,850
They came for Clumsy.

398
00:20:03,940 --> 00:20:09,610
Yes, but you see, Clumsy was a real Smurf.

399
00:20:10,940 --> 00:20:13,900
Whereas I was the one who created you.

400
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:16,530
You do remember that, don't you, dear?

401
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:21,450
You're not my father. Just let me go home.

402
00:20:21,540 --> 00:20:22,870
Of course.

403
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:24,250
Anything you say,

404
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:30,380
but first, I will need one itsy-bitsy, teeny-tiny little thing first.

405
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:32,510
- Teeny-tiny. - What?

406
00:20:33,130 --> 00:20:38,550
Just the secret formula that Papa used to turn you into a real Smurf.

407
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:41,390
Hackus real Smurf. Hackus blue!

408
00:20:41,470 --> 00:20:42,680
Like you, blondie.

409
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:45,230
It would benefit us both, don't you see, my dear?

410
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:48,520
You give me the formula, I turn my little Naughties blue.

411
00:20:48,730 --> 00:20:50,400
- Blue. - I use their essence

412
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:53,610
to continue with my wonderful magic show here.

413
00:20:53,690 --> 00:20:58,240
That way I never have to bother you or Smurf Village again.

414
00:20:58,450 --> 00:21:01,330
I don't trust you, and I'm not telling you anything.

415
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:06,000
Well, perhaps you need a little persuasion, eh?

416
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:08,330
Naughties, attack!

417
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,380
With pleasure.

418
00:21:10,460 --> 00:21:11,500
Attack!

419
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:13,550
- No, no, no, not each other. - Not me!

420
00:21:13,710 --> 00:21:15,590
I got you...

421
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:16,930
Hackus!

422
00:21:17,090 --> 00:21:18,640
Kitty, kitty, kitty.

423
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:22,720
Not the cat, not the...

424
00:21:22,810 --> 00:21:25,730
Deeply, deeply disappointing experiments.

425
00:21:25,980 --> 00:21:27,480
We've got to rescue Smurfette.

426
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:29,060
What's our plan to bring Smurfette home?

427
00:21:29,150 --> 00:21:30,610
All right, Smurfs, listen up.

428
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:35,440
I saved enough grotto water from the last blue moon for just such an occasion.

429
00:21:35,530 --> 00:21:38,860
I was able to smurf it into smurfportation crystals.

430
00:21:38,990 --> 00:21:42,030
So you don't need a portal. Very clever, Papa.

431
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,410
Smurf-xactly.

432
00:21:43,490 --> 00:21:46,500
These will take us directly to Master Winslow's mushroom.

433
00:21:46,620 --> 00:21:49,830
Yeah, Patrick and Grace helped us last time we smurfed through the portal.

434
00:21:49,920 --> 00:21:51,790
Precisely! They'll know what to do!

435
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:52,920
- Sign me up! - Sign me up.

436
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:53,960
- At your service, Papa. - Pick me!

437
00:21:54,050 --> 00:21:55,630
- Did someone say, "Baker should go"? - I would rather not.

438
00:21:55,710 --> 00:21:56,720
Me, me, pick me, Papa!

439
00:21:56,800 --> 00:22:00,180
Now, now, Smurfs. I only had water enough for nine crystals.

440
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:04,560
That's me and three others round trip, plus Smurfette on the way home.

441
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:06,680
Assuming you can find her, which you won't.

442
00:22:06,770 --> 00:22:10,400
That's not a very smurfy attitude, Grouchy.

443
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:12,560
Actually, for me, that was pretty good.

444
00:22:12,730 --> 00:22:15,730
I'll need courage, intelligence and strength.

445
00:22:15,820 --> 00:22:17,110
- So Gutsy. - Aye.

446
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:18,320
- Brainy. - Of course.

447
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:19,530
- Hefty. - You got it.

448
00:22:19,740 --> 00:22:21,490
- You'll smurf with me. - Yeah, can I...

449
00:22:21,570 --> 00:22:23,830
Yes, Passive-Aggressive Smurf?

450
00:22:23,910 --> 00:22:27,750
I think Brainy is a really excellent choice.

451
00:22:27,830 --> 00:22:28,830
Good luck with that.

452
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,210
You see what he does?

453
00:22:30,290 --> 00:22:32,170
- That's not a compliment. - Go figure.

454
00:22:32,330 --> 00:22:34,590
- Okay, Hefty, take one. - Let's do this.

455
00:22:34,710 --> 00:22:36,760
- Go get her, guys! - Oops!

456
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:37,840
Clumsy.

457
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:39,170
Somebody do something!

458
00:22:39,340 --> 00:22:41,510
Stand back! I know the Smurflich manoeuvre.

459
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:42,840
He doesn't look good.

460
00:22:42,930 --> 00:22:44,850
Oh, dear, he's turning blue-er.

461
00:22:44,930 --> 00:22:45,930
Not good.

462
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:48,890
Somebody get my hammer!

463
00:22:48,980 --> 00:22:50,850
Nice going, Clumsy.

464
00:22:51,850 --> 00:22:54,230
I got it!

465
00:22:54,310 --> 00:22:55,860
Cheerio!

466
00:22:56,020 --> 00:22:58,190
This was supposed to be Hefty!

467
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:59,690
Sorry! My bad!

468
00:22:59,780 --> 00:23:02,320
I get so puffy when I travel.

469
00:23:02,410 --> 00:23:03,410
Bye.

470
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:07,240
Well, sometimes, you got to smurf with the changes.

471
00:23:07,330 --> 00:23:08,410
Travel safe, Papa.

472
00:23:08,540 --> 00:23:11,210
And so Papa and his B team...

473
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:12,750
I'll be in charge while you're gone!

474
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:15,040
- And so Papa... - Go get Smurfette back!

475
00:23:15,130 --> 00:23:17,880
- Come on! - And bring her home!

476
00:23:20,220 --> 00:23:23,970
I'm glad his throat opened up and his lips are back to normal.

477
00:23:24,140 --> 00:23:25,800
Again, we're so sorry.

478
00:23:25,970 --> 00:23:27,970
If... Hello?

479
00:23:29,390 --> 00:23:33,850
Johnny can breathe again, which makes two of us since both of his parents are lawyers.

480
00:23:33,940 --> 00:23:36,820
Well, that's why they overreacted.

481
00:23:36,900 --> 00:23:38,110
They didn't overreact.

482
00:23:38,270 --> 00:23:39,940
He's dying.

483
00:23:41,190 --> 00:23:43,110
I think it's time for this.

484
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:46,410
You didn't bring the crown. Don't put the crown on him.

485
00:23:46,490 --> 00:23:47,990
Come on, you used to love this crown.

486
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:49,450
- No, I didn't. - Yes, you did.

487
00:23:49,620 --> 00:23:51,200
- You wore it everywhere. - I did not.

488
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:52,370
Never did. Never once.

489
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:55,580
This is the way you do it... Look.

490
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:58,960
Do you see what is going on out there?

491
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:02,800
Yeah, they're bonding.

492
00:24:04,340 --> 00:24:06,090
- Technically, they're spitting. - Come on.

493
00:24:06,180 --> 00:24:08,600
Blue needs to know that family's not just you and me,

494
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,600
and it's really good for him to play with his grandfather.

495
00:24:10,810 --> 00:24:12,180
Good job!

496
00:24:12,350 --> 00:24:14,980
- Oh, yeah. He's a terrific role model. - Come on, Patrick.

497
00:24:15,060 --> 00:24:16,520
Grace, he ruins everything.

498
00:24:16,690 --> 00:24:20,280
He shows up, and he ruins things. That's what he does.

499
00:24:20,860 --> 00:24:23,610
Just like when he first moved into my house.

500
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:25,910
He sent my parrot away.

501
00:24:25,990 --> 00:24:26,990
Your parrot?

502
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:29,160
My father's parrot.

503
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:35,920
When my dad took off, he left Zeus, and I loved that bird.

504
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:40,840
I was a kid, and Zeus was the only part of my dad I had left.

505
00:24:44,760 --> 00:24:46,050
There you go.

506
00:24:49,430 --> 00:24:50,470
What?

507
00:24:58,350 --> 00:25:00,110
Get Blue. Blue?

508
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:02,780
Blue?

509
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:06,240
Blue! Victor!

