00:38:41,470 --> 00:38:43,470
Anyone else want a cup o' joe?

768
00:38:44,390 --> 00:38:46,640
Hey, what's that?

769
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:48,560
It's a mirror, you barbarian.

770
00:38:48,640 --> 00:38:50,440
Snap out of it, Vanity, and push!

771
00:38:52,690 --> 00:38:54,150
Rage before beauty.

772
00:38:54,230 --> 00:38:56,730
Whatever this is, it's making my butt scrunch.

773
00:38:57,360 --> 00:39:00,200
That's a little scary. I mean...

774
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:02,450
Gargamel!

775
00:39:04,580 --> 00:39:07,700
Clumsy! Are you trying to get us smurfed?

776
00:39:07,790 --> 00:39:10,160
It's some sort of magic window.

777
00:39:10,250 --> 00:39:12,040
Maybe it'll show us where Smurfette is.

778
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:14,080
Naughties?

779
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:16,300
- Gargamel! - Quickly, pick it up.

780
00:39:16,800 --> 00:39:18,880
Quickly, to me, to me!

781
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:21,340
Smurfette? Hello?

782
00:39:21,550 --> 00:39:23,470
Where did you go? Hello?

783
00:39:23,640 --> 00:39:25,300
- Move, Smurfs. - Here he comes. Hurry.

784
00:39:25,550 --> 00:39:27,140
- Let's go! Let's go! - Where are you? Are you here?

785
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:29,810
- Children? Smurfette? - Back up, back up.

786
00:39:30,310 --> 00:39:31,600
Close the door! Close the door!

787
00:39:31,690 --> 00:39:33,230
Your papa is back.

788
00:39:33,980 --> 00:39:35,190
Her papa?

789
00:39:35,270 --> 00:39:37,900
If this is a joke, I assure you I don't find it funny.

790
00:39:38,780 --> 00:39:40,610
- Hello? - Hold it!

791
00:39:40,820 --> 00:39:44,530
- Are you down there, you little delinquents? - Keep still.

792
00:39:44,620 --> 00:39:46,620
They must have retreated back to the hotel.

793
00:39:50,250 --> 00:39:52,040
Of course we're running out of time.

794
00:39:52,120 --> 00:39:55,920
If that Patrick person is here, then Papa cannot be far behind.

795
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:59,000
Quickly, to the hotel! We must get to her before he does.

796
00:40:03,470 --> 00:40:04,930
My face! My face!

797
00:40:05,010 --> 00:40:07,390
- What? - It's gorgeous.

798
00:40:08,060 --> 00:40:10,930
We fell, and it wasn't even my fault!

799
00:40:11,390 --> 00:40:13,140
Anyone? Anyone?

800
00:40:13,230 --> 00:40:17,060
Oh, my Smurf.

801
00:40:20,860 --> 00:40:22,950
I'm scrunching again.

802
00:40:23,780 --> 00:40:27,320
Papa, what does this have to do with Smurfette?

803
00:40:27,410 --> 00:40:29,910
Everything, I'm afraid.

804
00:40:29,990 --> 00:40:33,120
Why would he build such a hideous device?

805
00:40:33,210 --> 00:40:35,750
Is that a giant Smurfalator?

806
00:40:35,830 --> 00:40:37,670
To extract our essence.

807
00:40:38,380 --> 00:40:41,550
What are all those containers for?

808
00:40:41,630 --> 00:40:44,970
Ninety-nine bottles of Smurf on the wall.

809
00:40:45,050 --> 00:40:47,890
So if Smurfette gives him the formula...

810
00:40:47,970 --> 00:40:53,270
He can turn as many Naughties into Smurfs as his greedy heart desires.

811
00:40:53,350 --> 00:40:55,020
Guys?

812
00:40:59,680 --> 00:41:02,710
Total Smurf a geddon.

813
00:41:03,440 --> 00:41:04,530
Oh, dear.

814
00:41:06,740 --> 00:41:08,370
Need a catch, please.

815
00:41:12,080 --> 00:41:14,370
This place really needs to recycle.

816
00:41:14,790 --> 00:41:16,960
Think, Smurfette, think. Oh, no!

817
00:41:17,040 --> 00:41:19,210
- Where's Smurfette? Where's Smurfette? - There she is!

818
00:41:19,290 --> 00:41:21,630
She's fast! I love this game!

819
00:41:21,710 --> 00:41:25,300
Wait! Let's let her run for a bit. She's got nowhere to go.

820
00:41:25,380 --> 00:41:27,430
- This is perfect for my plan! - Yeah, yeah.

821
00:41:27,630 --> 00:41:30,220
What are you so cross about? I'm the duck!

822
00:41:30,390 --> 00:41:33,470
You always barge in and ruin everything! You're like a walking disaster!

823
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:35,230
Hey, look me in the eyes and say that.

824
00:41:35,430 --> 00:41:38,730
- I can't. - That's right, because it's not true.

825
00:41:39,230 --> 00:41:41,520
No, I can't because your eyes are on the sides of your head!

826
00:41:42,440 --> 00:41:45,360
All the better for me to see your disrespect!

827
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:48,320
- What are you looking at? - Hurry up.

828
00:41:48,410 --> 00:41:50,280
It's global warming. Buy a Prius.

829
00:41:51,410 --> 00:41:53,660
Okay. Did I lose them?

830
00:41:57,580 --> 00:41:58,790
Good dog.

831
00:41:59,500 --> 00:42:02,250
No, no... Sorry. Excuse me.

832
00:42:03,920 --> 00:42:05,670
Okay, I got this.

833
00:42:16,270 --> 00:42:19,650
Papa, where are you?

834
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:24,110
Why am I not surprised the way out of Gargamel's lair is through a sewer?

835
00:42:24,190 --> 00:42:25,780
- Master Winslow. - Papa!

836
00:42:25,860 --> 00:42:27,610
- Patrick, look. - What happened?

837
00:42:27,780 --> 00:42:30,950
Gargamel is hatching a terrible, terrible plan.

838
00:42:32,160 --> 00:42:33,580
What's with the duck?

839
00:42:33,780 --> 00:42:35,830
That's Victor. Gargamel turned him into a duck.

840
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:39,080
- Now Gargamel knows we're onto him. - I was only trying to help!

841
00:42:39,290 --> 00:42:41,130
Victor, you look fowl.

842
00:42:41,750 --> 00:42:44,040
Yes, I did. Yes, I did.

843
00:42:44,290 --> 00:42:47,550
Focus, everyone. We've got to find Smurfette quickly.

844
00:42:48,220 --> 00:42:51,390
- There she is! Got her! - Chase over?

845
00:42:52,180 --> 00:42:54,720
Hey, Hackus. See that candy store?

846
00:42:54,810 --> 00:42:57,060
- Candy? Candy! - I've got an idea.

847
00:42:57,310 --> 00:43:00,730
Go get yourself in trouble. Be naughty! I'll take care of the rest.

848
00:43:00,810 --> 00:43:03,810
I love to make trouble! Naughty, naughty, naughty!

849
00:43:05,770 --> 00:43:08,030
Hey, blondie. Where you going?

850
00:43:08,240 --> 00:43:09,570
Leave me alone.

851
00:43:09,650 --> 00:43:12,160
You mean like your so-called Papa has?

852
00:43:12,660 --> 00:43:14,200
No, he hasn't!

853
00:43:15,370 --> 00:43:17,160
He will come for me.

854
00:43:18,040 --> 00:43:23,040
He won't, because he knows you're where you really belong.

855
00:43:23,750 --> 00:43:25,380
I didn't kidnap you, Smurfette.

856
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:27,630
I brought you home.

857
00:43:29,970 --> 00:43:32,300
I'm gonna make big trouble.

858
00:43:38,310 --> 00:43:40,430
Yummy candy!

859
00:43:48,530 --> 00:43:49,570
Here comes trouble!

860
00:43:52,820 --> 00:43:54,280
Hello!

861
00:44:04,710 --> 00:44:08,500
Oh, my gosh! He's gonna be killed! We have to help!

862
00:44:10,010 --> 00:44:11,630
I thought you were supposed to be good.

863
00:44:11,840 --> 00:44:13,130
But...

864
00:44:13,590 --> 00:44:14,970
Help!

865
00:44:15,180 --> 00:44:16,510
Oh, smurf.

866
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:18,060
Okay, come on!

867
00:44:18,390 --> 00:44:21,480
Oh, no. I'm really in trouble now.

868
00:44:21,730 --> 00:44:23,940
- Vexy! - Oh, no! Hackus!

869
00:44:24,060 --> 00:44:25,190
Help!

870
00:44:25,310 --> 00:44:26,730
Help Hackus.

871
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:30,530
Smurfette, what are we gonna do?

872
00:44:31,070 --> 00:44:33,070
Vexy, give me a lift! Come on, jump!

873
00:44:36,070 --> 00:44:38,240
- Bull's-eye! - Holy smurf!

874
00:44:38,410 --> 00:44:41,500
- Good one, Smurfette! - Blend that, candy man!

875
00:44:41,750 --> 00:44:42,790
Come on, Hackus!

876
00:44:44,540 --> 00:44:46,710
Vexy, let's go!

877
00:44:50,590 --> 00:44:51,760
Hold on!

878
00:44:52,010 --> 00:44:53,550
Look out!

879
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:55,630
Nice move, stealing a cart.

880
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:57,970
I didn't exactly steal it.

881
00:44:58,680 --> 00:45:00,600
- Sorry! - Well, it's not yours, is it?

882
00:45:00,680 --> 00:45:01,930
Naughty, naughty, naughty.

883
00:45:02,020 --> 00:45:04,100
See? You're just like us.

884
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:09,860
How am I going to get Smurfette to give me that formula, Azrael?

885
00:45:09,940 --> 00:45:12,110
This whole thing just makes me want to...

886
00:45:12,820 --> 00:45:15,150
Cry? No. Flush her down the toilet bowl.

887
00:45:15,240 --> 00:45:16,820
There must be something we can do.

888
00:45:16,910 --> 00:45:20,620
I know you only have a tiny little pea-sized brain in there, but think!

889
00:45:21,790 --> 00:45:24,160
Is it her birthday? Really? Who cares?

890
00:45:25,910 --> 00:45:28,250
A present? A cake?

891
00:45:28,330 --> 00:45:29,380
Be nice to her?

892
00:45:32,670 --> 00:45:37,300
Bribery and flattery to soften her stony little heart, eh?

893
00:45:37,380 --> 00:45:40,430
That's counterintuitive, but that just might work.

894
00:45:41,140 --> 00:45:43,180
I'm so glad I thought of this!

895
00:45:44,140 --> 00:45:45,600
Let's see...

896
00:45:46,350 --> 00:45:47,350
All right, all right.

897
00:45:47,560 --> 00:45:49,060
What kind of gift should I get her?

898
00:45:49,230 --> 00:45:51,320
- Kitty, kitty, kitty! - Hey, fish breath!

899
00:45:53,480 --> 00:45:55,530
Not now, Azrael, I'm trying to think of

900
00:45:55,610 --> 00:45:58,910
a genuine and heartfelt gift that I can deceive that Smurfette with!

901
00:45:58,990 --> 00:46:00,320
I said not now!

902
00:46:01,490 --> 00:46:05,040
Not now! Not now! Not now! Not now! Not now! Not now!

903
00:46:06,330 --> 00:46:07,830
You are walking home.

904
00:46:09,330 --> 00:46:10,330
Cats.

905
00:46:12,340 --> 00:46:13,500
Faster! Faster!

906
00:46:13,630 --> 00:46:14,590
Excuse us! Sorry!

907
00:46:14,670 --> 00:46:16,170
How are we gonna stop this thing?

908
00:46:16,630 --> 00:46:18,680
I don't think that's gonna be a problem!

909
00:46:19,590 --> 00:46:21,680
And she sticks the landing!

910
00:46:25,220 --> 00:46:28,310
- Yummy pudding! - Hackus, it's mud.

911
00:46:28,390 --> 00:46:30,020
Yummy mud!

912
00:46:33,320 --> 00:46:35,230
Take your best shot, cat!

913
00:46:35,980 --> 00:46:37,030
Watch out!

914
00:46:40,410 --> 00:46:41,410
Yes!

915
00:46:41,570 --> 00:46:43,530
- Nice shot! Let's go! - Nice shot! Let's go!

916
00:46:44,080 --> 00:46:45,950
- Come on! - Move it or lose it, Hackus!

917
00:46:46,040 --> 00:46:49,210
Oh, no! Angry kitty! Angry kitty! Run!

918
00:46:49,660 --> 00:46:51,540
Okay, ladies, act pregnant.

919
00:46:51,670 --> 00:46:52,830
- This way, guys! - Faster!

920
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:54,710
- It's time to get your wings! - Faster!

921
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:56,050
Quick, get on the storks!

922
00:46:56,210 --> 00:46:57,340
Let's go!

923
00:46:57,420 --> 00:46:58,420
Wait, where's Hackus?

924
00:46:59,420 --> 00:47:00,930
Fly, big stork, fly!

925
00:47:01,430 --> 00:47:03,800
Here comes kitty! Look out!

926
00:47:04,430 --> 00:47:06,390
Come on, Hackus! Let's go!

927
00:47:08,850 --> 00:47:10,190
Yeah!

928
00:47:10,730 --> 00:47:13,020
Hey, look, it's a catfish!

929
00:47:13,110 --> 00:47:15,270
Bye, kitty!

930
00:47:16,230 --> 00:47:18,490
This is amazing!

931
00:47:18,990 --> 00:47:22,160
Stork going backwards! Stork going backwards!

932
00:47:26,120 --> 00:47:28,910
This is so beautiful!

933
00:47:30,410 --> 00:47:32,330
I'm falling! I'm falling!

934
00:47:33,920 --> 00:47:36,000
Smurfette's my hero!

935
00:47:37,840 --> 00:47:39,550
- How did it go? - Couldn't have gone better.

936
00:47:39,630 --> 00:47:42,260
Except that everything was a complete smurftastrophe.

937
00:47:43,090 --> 00:47:44,470
It's Smurfy's Law.

938
00:47:44,550 --> 00:47:46,810
Well, I have some good news.

939
00:47:46,890 --> 00:47:52,390
I borrowed a waiter's outfit for you, complete with a security card for the elevator.

940
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:53,600
How did you manage that?

941
00:47:53,940 --> 00:47:57,070
Let's just say that the Plaza Athénée laundry room was paid a little visit

942
00:47:57,230 --> 00:48:01,190
by international apparel inspector Mademoiselle Doolittle.

943
00:48:01,280 --> 00:48:03,160
I was like Meryl smurfin' Streep.

944
00:48:04,110 --> 00:48:05,740
Good job, Grace!

945
00:48:05,870 --> 00:48:08,330
Does everyone get a new outfit, or just Patrick?

946
00:48:09,450 --> 00:48:11,080
- Bloody window. - What was that?

947
00:48:11,250 --> 00:48:12,210
That's Victor.

948
00:48:12,290 --> 00:48:15,710
They wouldn't let him through the lobby, so he flew up.

949
00:48:16,920 --> 00:48:18,800
No depth perception.

950
00:48:18,960 --> 00:48:20,800
Grandpa Vicster is a duck!

951
00:48:21,130 --> 00:48:22,300
Gargamel zapped him.

952
00:48:22,760 --> 00:48:23,800
You can change him back, right?

953
00:48:24,340 --> 00:48:26,510
No, but it's a transformation spell.

954
00:48:26,720 --> 00:48:28,140
It'll wear off eventually.

955
00:48:28,310 --> 00:48:30,560
Everybody relax. It's not a problem.

956
00:48:30,640 --> 00:48:33,140
But if you see me lay an egg, it's just between us.

957
00:48:35,100 --> 00:48:36,810
You don't seem too upset about this.

958
00:48:36,980 --> 00:48:39,190
It's not in a duck's nature to get upset.

959
00:48:39,270 --> 00:48:41,860
We like to let things roll off our backs.

960
00:48:42,030 --> 00:48:44,240
Seriously? You seriously just said that?

961
00:48:44,400 --> 00:48:47,160
- I like that. That's very smurfy of you. - Very smurfy.

962
00:48:47,240 --> 00:48:48,530
Why, thank you. See?

963
00:48:48,740 --> 00:48:50,740
The little Santa Claus Smurf appreciates me.

964
00:48:50,830 --> 00:48:54,710
Maybe someday, Patrick, you'll learn to appreciate my smurfy qualities, too!

965
00:48:54,960 --> 00:48:56,920
Okay. I've... There's... You know...

966
00:48:57,130 --> 00:48:58,880
I'm not having this conversation with a duck.

967
00:49:00,670 --> 00:49:02,420
Now I'm catching a cold.

968
00:49:02,510 --> 00:49:03,760
I wish I had a cold.

969
00:49:03,970 --> 00:49:06,090
I've had Hefty's crystal shoved down my throat,

970
00:49:06,180 --> 00:49:09,010
got attacked as a corn dog, fell down a sewer,

971
00:49:09,220 --> 00:49:11,520
and if that wasn't smelly enough,

972
00:49:11,680 --> 00:49:15,690
had to travel by armpit just to find out we're all gonna be extinct!

973
00:49:16,520 --> 00:49:20,400
- Holy smurf, I'm a downer. - You most certainly are.

974
00:49:20,650 --> 00:49:22,700
Grouchy, the only way we'll be extinct

975
00:49:22,850 --> 00:49:25,650
is if Smurfette gives Gargamel the secret formula.

976
00:49:25,820 --> 00:49:27,990
- But Smurfette would never tell. - Of course not.

977
00:49:28,070 --> 00:49:29,280
- Never. - Absolutely not.

978
00:49:29,370 --> 00:49:32,240
Smurfette could never be tricked into being one of them.

979
00:49:33,370 --> 00:49:34,500
Hey, Smurfette.

980
00:49:34,580 --> 00:49:37,040
Did you do this with your sisters back in Smurf Village?

981
00:49:37,120 --> 00:49:40,630
Lots of flying, but I never had a sister.

982
00:49:40,710 --> 00:49:42,380
Well, you do now.

983
00:49:42,460 --> 00:49:45,050
- Want to race? - You want to race me?

984
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:47,720
You're in trouble now!

985
00:49:49,430 --> 00:49:51,600
- I'm gonna lose you, Smurfette. - Not a chance.

986
00:50:01,270 --> 00:50:03,150
Watch out!

987
00:50:03,230 --> 00:50:04,820
Hold on tight, Hackus.

988
00:50:05,740 --> 00:50:07,780
- Not that tight, Hackus. - Sorry.

989
00:50:07,950 --> 00:50:09,820
Stork fight!

990
00:50:10,740 --> 00:50:12,200
Coming through!

991
00:50:13,080 --> 00:50:14,740
This is insane!

992
00:50:16,250 --> 00:50:18,420
Smurf, smurf, and away.

993
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:22,420
Hackus, king of world!

994
00:50:23,710 --> 00:50:25,510
You're playing dirty now!

995
00:50:25,710 --> 00:50:27,380
I'm just getting started.

996
00:50:27,470 --> 00:50:28,970
Go, go!

997
00:50:29,090 --> 00:50:31,050
I call that a Crepe Smurfette.

998
00:50:32,850 --> 00:50:34,810
Snails to go?

999
00:50:35,930 --> 00:50:37,980
- Batter up! - Come on!

1000
00:50:38,100 --> 00:50:40,190
Hit me with your best shot.

1001
00:50:42,810 --> 00:50:43,820
Snailed her!

1002
00:50:43,900 --> 00:50:46,030
- You are naughty, Smurfette. - Yeah.

1003
00:50:50,240 --> 00:50:53,620
Hey! I've seen that lady before.

1004
00:50:53,700 --> 00:50:55,330
She's beautiful.

1005
00:50:55,410 --> 00:50:58,460
They've got one of these everywhere.

1006
00:50:59,120 --> 00:51:00,540
I'm gonna strangle that duck.

1007
00:51:00,620 --> 00:51:02,670
Vic's like a black cloud that follows me around.

1008
00:51:04,040 --> 00:51:05,130
Okay, look, I get it.

1009
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:07,130
But you know what, he's here, isn't he?

1010
00:51:07,300 --> 00:51:08,550
He shows up.

1011
00:51:08,630 --> 00:51:10,510
Yeah, whether you want him to or not.

1012
00:51:10,680 --> 00:51:13,140
Okay, I always heard that showing up was 90% of the job.

1013
00:51:13,640 --> 00:51:15,390
A lot of fathers don't even do that.

1014
00:51:15,720 --> 00:51:17,310
He's not my father.

1015
00:51:17,560 --> 00:51:19,390
Well, that's too bad.

1016
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:21,810
'Cause that pretty much leaves you without one.

1017
00:51:35,160 --> 00:51:36,830
- Patrick. - All right, guys.

1018
00:51:36,990 --> 00:51:38,540
- Come on. - Let's do this!

1019
00:51:38,620 --> 00:51:40,750
- I'm gonna stay with Blue. - And Vic.

1020
00:51:40,830 --> 00:51:43,330
Okay, Smurfs, off to Gargamel's hotel.

1021
00:51:43,420 --> 00:51:44,960
Patrick, there's actually something I'd like to...

1022
00:51:45,040 --> 00:51:46,130
No "actuallys."

1023
00:51:46,340 --> 00:51:47,420
You're staying here.

1024
00:51:47,590 --> 00:51:48,880
That's not what I was even going...

1025
00:51:49,050 --> 00:51:50,630
Victor, don't make me pluck you.

1026
00:51:50,800 --> 00:51:52,130
- Let's go. - Let's do it.

1027
00:51:52,300 --> 00:51:56,100
We're gonna get Smurfette this time, 100% guaranteed.

1028
00:51:56,300 --> 00:51:57,850
What did you just say, Grouchy?

1029
00:51:58,060 --> 00:52:03,020
You heard it. I'm tired of being Grouchy. I am changing my tune to a happy one.

1030
00:52:03,190 --> 00:52:05,060
From now on, lam...

1031
00:52:05,190 --> 00:52:07,650
Ready? Positive Smurf.

1032
00:52:07,730 --> 00:52:09,900
I sprained my face.

1033
00:52:10,110 --> 00:52:12,450
You'll get used to it. Let's go, Smurfs.

1034
00:52:12,950 --> 00:52:14,780
- Come on. Come on. - A paper bag. First-class.

1035
00:52:14,860 --> 00:52:16,740
- Hurry... - Clumsy!

1036
00:52:17,450 --> 00:52:19,200
Good luck, Daddy!

1037
00:52:21,620 --> 00:52:23,160
Le chat VIP.

1038
00:52:23,250 --> 00:52:25,830
Please, I will take you to your room.

1039
00:52:30,960 --> 00:52:33,800
- Front desk. - Listen well, you slack-jawed knave.

1040
00:52:33,880 --> 00:52:34,970
Monsieur Gargamel.

1041
00:52:35,140 --> 00:52:39,810
I want ale, curds and blistered meats sent into my room in 10 minutes,

1042
00:52:39,890 --> 00:52:43,230
or I will turn you into a legless tree sloth.

1043
00:52:44,230 --> 00:52:47,020
How was that, Smurfs?

1044
00:52:47,860 --> 00:52:48,940
That's not funny, man.

1045
00:52:54,740 --> 00:52:58,700
Duck, duck, duck.

1046
00:52:59,280 --> 00:53:00,700
Goose!

1047
00:53:04,040 --> 00:53:07,080
The security card for the elevator. Patrick needs my help.

1048
00:53:08,750 --> 00:53:13,510
When I show up with this, he'll see this black cloud has got a silver...

1049
00:53:13,920 --> 00:53:15,550
A silver lining!

1050
00:53:28,770 --> 00:53:30,570
Oh, my...

1051
00:53:30,650 --> 00:53:32,110
Master Winslow, please.

1052
00:53:32,190 --> 00:53:33,740
- You can't get a reservation... - Focus.

1053
00:53:33,820 --> 00:53:35,450
That smells delish!

1054
00:53:38,240 --> 00:53:39,660
Le bingo.

1055
00:53:43,410 --> 00:53:47,540
Okay, guys, listen, when you get to the room, if there's any problems...

1056
00:53:48,630 --> 00:53:52,300
- Snot on a half shell. Delicacy. - Sorry, Mr Fish!

1057
00:53:53,130 --> 00:53:54,460
You look fried.

1058
00:53:54,550 --> 00:53:56,130
Like I said, if there are any problems...

1059
00:53:56,340 --> 00:53:58,260
My friend, there are no such thing as problems.

1060
00:53:58,340 --> 00:53:59,970
Only smurfitunities.

1061
00:54:00,050 --> 00:54:02,470
- You're freaking me out, Grouchy. - Positive!

1062
00:54:02,640 --> 00:54:04,180
Of...

1063
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:12,400
Okay, guys, we're in.

1064
00:54:12,480 --> 00:54:14,440
Patrick Winslow-Doyle.

1065
00:54:15,940 --> 00:54:17,110
Patrick.

1066
00:54:18,700 --> 00:54:21,660
- What are you doing here? - Saving your tail feather. Now come here.

1067
00:54:21,780 --> 00:54:23,330
I've got something you need for your mission.

1068
00:54:23,490 --> 00:54:24,660
Hurry up. There's no time to argue.

1069
00:54:26,660 --> 00:54:28,870
- What? - It's the security card for the elevator.

1070
00:54:29,080 --> 00:54:31,210
I have the security card.

1071
00:54:31,670 --> 00:54:34,670
What is this? This is our room key.

1072
00:54:36,630 --> 00:54:39,130
Well, now when you come back, you'll be able to get in.

1073
00:54:39,340 --> 00:54:40,550
- No problem. - I can't...

1074
00:54:40,970 --> 00:54:41,970
No, no, no, no, no.

1075
00:54:43,180 --> 00:54:44,260
You're welcome.

1076
00:54:44,430 --> 00:54:46,430
You can thank me later.

1077
00:54:46,520 --> 00:54:48,020
How did you get out?

1078
00:54:48,180 --> 00:54:49,440
Now, you just put me back down.

1079
00:54:49,520 --> 00:54:50,730
Patrick, help!

1080
00:54:50,940 --> 00:54:53,570
- We need you for our duck a l'orange. - You want a piece of me?

1081
00:54:53,730 --> 00:54:55,820
No, no, no, no! That's not what I meant.

1082
00:54:55,900 --> 00:54:59,200
Yeah, it starts with the ducks, and soon, no one's safe!

1083
00:54:59,570 --> 00:55:01,660
- Unbelievable. - Patrick!

1084
00:55:04,490 --> 00:55:05,490
Master Winslow?

1085
00:55:05,580 --> 00:55:07,410
- Patrick! - Where'd he go?

1086
00:55:07,790 --> 00:55:09,290
- He disappeared. - Now we're on our own.

1087
00:55:09,370 --> 00:55:10,790
- Well... - Hide!

1088
00:55:12,830 --> 00:55:14,130
Monsieur Gargamel.

1089
00:55:19,970 --> 00:55:22,430
We're smurfed. Plan B, anybody?

1090
00:55:22,510 --> 00:55:24,440
I'm struggling to remain positive here.

1091
00:55:30,230 --> 00:55:32,150
Monsieur Gargamel?

1092
00:55:33,020 --> 00:55:34,110
Room service.

1093
00:55:36,730 --> 00:55:38,400
Hello, kitty.

1094
00:55:38,900 --> 00:55:40,070
Here is your room service.

1095
00:55:40,240 --> 00:55:44,030
- What do we do? - Smurf him with the element of surprise.

1096
00:55:44,990 --> 00:55:46,620
Oh, Clumsy!

1097
00:55:48,490 --> 00:55:49,660
- Oh, dear. - Now what do we do?

1098
00:55:50,750 --> 00:55:52,080
Just act scary.

1099
00:55:52,250 --> 00:55:53,540
What?

1100
00:55:53,670 --> 00:55:56,090
I'm a scary ghost!

1101
00:55:56,380 --> 00:55:57,420
Nice.

1102
00:55:58,880 --> 00:56:01,630
Why do so many bad things happen to little blue people?

1103
00:56:01,800 --> 00:56:03,640
Positive, positive.

1104
00:56:03,840 --> 00:56:07,310
Window! Window! Window!

1105
00:56:10,100 --> 00:56:13,020
Oh, no!

1106
00:56:13,560 --> 00:56:16,190
Are you smurfing kidding me? You nearly killed...

1107
00:56:17,070 --> 00:56:19,280
I mean, look at this view.

1108
00:56:23,700 --> 00:56:29,660
If it looks like a duck, quacks like a duck, and smells like a corn dog...

1109
00:56:29,870 --> 00:56:31,870
All right, which one of you is Vic?

1110
00:56:31,960 --> 00:56:33,790
What, you don't recognise your own father?

1111
00:56:35,420 --> 00:56:37,880
- Let's go. - What about my brothers?

1112
00:56:37,960 --> 00:56:39,800
We can't just leave them here to be eaten.

1113
00:56:39,960 --> 00:56:41,210
You just met them.

1114
00:56:41,460 --> 00:56:44,300
This is my flock. I can't just leave them behind.

1115
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:47,180
Come on, if you're game, so am I.

1116
00:56:50,180 --> 00:56:52,560
I am covered in filth.

1117
00:56:52,770 --> 00:56:55,060
I look like something the cat dragged in!

1118
00:56:57,810 --> 00:56:59,900
Come on, it's not that bad.

1119
00:57:00,150 --> 00:57:02,280
Although, if I don't... The cat!

1120
00:57:02,490 --> 00:57:05,660
- Not the face. Not the face! - Close the lid!

1121
00:57:08,120 --> 00:57:10,370
- That was awesome! - Thank you!

1122
00:57:10,830 --> 00:57:13,000
Hackus lives!

1123
00:57:13,080 --> 00:57:14,330
Vexy, come and help me close the door.

1124
00:57:14,500 --> 00:57:16,080
- Thank you, bird. - Bye.

1125
00:57:16,170 --> 00:57:17,920
That was crazy.

1126
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:21,920
Bye-bye, birds. I had fun.

1127
00:57:22,340 --> 00:57:23,340
Yeah.

1128
00:57:23,550 --> 00:57:25,550
- High fours! - High fours!

1129
00:57:25,630 --> 00:57:28,090
Hackus, Hackus, Hackus.

1130
00:57:28,180 --> 00:57:30,350
It's so nice having another girl around.

1131
00:57:32,930 --> 00:57:33,930
What are you doing?

1132
00:57:34,430 --> 00:57:37,020
Rm just hugging you.

1133
00:57:37,690 --> 00:57:39,900
Haven't you ever been hugged?

1134
00:57:43,530 --> 00:57:45,110
Vexy...

1135
00:57:49,870 --> 00:57:52,870
- Hackus hug. Hackus hug. - Hackus.

1136
00:57:52,950 --> 00:57:54,790
Hackus squeeze!

1137
00:57:54,870 --> 00:57:56,210
Hackus.

1138
00:57:56,370 --> 00:57:58,960
I'm positive we should just leave him in here.

1139
00:57:59,040 --> 00:58:00,040
Thanks.

1140
00:58:00,290 --> 00:58:04,260
Hurry. They're probably doing something mean and horrible to her right now.

1141
00:58:04,420 --> 00:58:07,760
Yeah, Smurfette needs us. She's probably scared and...

1142
00:58:09,260 --> 00:58:11,350
- I love family! - What...

1143
00:58:11,890 --> 00:58:13,220
What is she doing?

1144
00:58:13,310 --> 00:58:15,310
I think they're hugging.

1145
00:58:15,390 --> 00:58:16,560
Papa?

1146
00:58:16,770 --> 00:58:18,310
Hackus love to hug.

1147
00:58:18,390 --> 00:58:19,770
Hackus.

1148
00:58:19,850 --> 00:58:22,400
Smurfette, come on, I got to show you something.

1149
00:58:23,440 --> 00:58:27,150
Look at us. Come on, tell me we're not family.

1150
00:58:28,700 --> 00:58:30,950
Smurfette!

1151
00:58:31,030 --> 00:58:32,160
Over here!

1152
00:58:32,240 --> 00:58:33,280
Smurfette!

1153
00:58:33,370 --> 00:58:36,410
I'm sorry Papa Smurf didn't come for you.

1154
00:58:36,500 --> 00:58:41,000
But maybe your place is here with us.

1155
00:58:42,500 --> 00:58:43,960
Yeah.

1156
00:58:44,380 --> 00:58:45,590
Maybe it is.

1157
00:58:46,090 --> 00:58:48,260
Why is she being nice to them?

1158
00:58:48,470 --> 00:58:52,100
She's just identifying with her captors. It's classic Smurf-holm syndrome.

1159
00:58:52,260 --> 00:58:56,390
No, she thinks we don't care anymore, and they do.

1160
00:58:56,470 --> 00:58:57,770
She's confused.

1161
00:58:58,100 --> 00:59:01,150
Clumsy, Grouchy, get up there, and help me get this door open.

1162
00:59:01,230 --> 00:59:02,310
- That's my daughter in there! - Okay, Papa.

1163
00:59:02,400 --> 00:59:05,530
- I'll get on top. - Okay, Grouchy, you jump, I'll pull.

1164
00:59:05,610 --> 00:59:08,070
- Come on, we can do this. - Children.

1165
00:59:08,240 --> 00:59:11,280
- Gargamel! - Clumsy, don't let go...

1166
00:59:11,780 --> 00:59:13,200
Daddy's home.

1167
00:59:13,280 --> 00:59:18,250
And consistent with his kind nature, he brought you a present.

1168
00:59:18,450 --> 00:59:19,580
Grouchy, get down. He'll see you.

1169
00:59:19,660 --> 00:59:21,960
- How are we gonna rescue her now? - Quiet.

1170
00:59:22,130 --> 00:59:24,750
I do believe we got off on the wrong foot earlier.

1171
00:59:24,840 --> 00:59:25,880
What's happening?

1172
00:59:25,960 --> 00:59:29,720
Would you allow me to wish you a very, very happy birthday?

1173
00:59:30,630 --> 00:59:32,260
It seems like only yesterday

1174
00:59:32,340 --> 00:59:36,600
you were just my little glob of clay and other putrid ingredients.

1175
00:59:36,810 --> 00:59:40,390
You remembered my birthday?

1176
00:59:40,480 --> 00:59:42,900
Of course I did. We're family.

1177
00:59:43,060 --> 00:59:44,480
- What? - But we're her family.

1178
00:59:44,560 --> 00:59:47,360
- Families don't forget things like that. - Does she think we abandoned her?

1179
00:59:47,530 --> 00:59:51,070
Speaking of which, your little blue step-papa never did arrive, now did he?

1180
00:59:51,150 --> 00:59:52,490
Step-Papa?

1181
00:59:52,660 --> 00:59:55,990
Why, I am truly sorry, my dear. That must really sting.

1182
00:59:57,370 --> 01:00:01,620
I remember when my father threw me down the well for the first time.

1183
01:00:02,540 --> 01:00:04,920
The disappointed look on his face

1184
01:00:05,090 --> 01:00:07,960
when I finally managed to claw my way out.

1185
01:00:09,380 --> 01:00:12,130
Anyway, happy birthday, my dear.

1186
01:00:12,220 --> 01:00:13,890
- Happy birthday, Smurfette! - Happy birthday, Smurfette!

1187
01:00:14,010 --> 01:00:16,470
- I want to open! Let me open! - No, no, no.

1188
01:00:16,680 --> 01:00:17,850
Ugly.

1189
01:00:22,190 --> 01:00:25,520
"Bow. Kneel. Worship me."

1190
01:00:27,360 --> 01:00:30,530
Yes, delightful rendition, really.

1191
01:00:30,610 --> 01:00:32,780
Keep it up, no-neck, I'll turn you into a cross-eyed newt.

1192
01:00:34,030 --> 01:00:36,950
Yes, yes, my dear.

1193
01:00:37,030 --> 01:00:38,530
Go ahead, take it.

1194
01:00:38,700 --> 01:00:42,870
It's a tiny little magical wand of your very own.

1195
01:00:42,960 --> 01:00:45,880
Go ahead. It's your birthday present.

1196
01:00:50,420 --> 01:00:51,880
No.

1197
01:00:52,010 --> 01:00:53,510
Don't do it.

1198
01:00:55,640 --> 01:00:57,600
Do you like it?

1199
01:00:58,890 --> 01:01:02,270
Silly me. I've forgotten to turn it on.

1200
01:01:03,310 --> 01:01:05,100
Here we are.

1201
01:01:05,730 --> 01:01:09,020
Yes, there we go.

1202
01:01:12,940 --> 01:01:15,740
Yes, go ahead, try it out. Don't be afraid.

1203
01:01:15,910 --> 01:01:17,950
- A Dragon Wand. - Oh, dear.

1204
01:01:18,200 --> 01:01:21,080
After all, it is your birthright.

1205
01:01:22,540 --> 01:01:24,370
How do you know I won't use it on you?

1206
01:01:25,460 --> 01:01:26,580
Well...

1207
01:01:26,670 --> 01:01:31,090
Because, Smurfette, I am your father.

1208
01:01:31,170 --> 01:01:34,300
Search your feelings. You know it to be true.

1209
01:01:34,470 --> 01:01:37,010
- She's gonna zap him. - Get him, Smurfette.

1210
01:01:37,220 --> 01:01:38,510
Smurfette...

1211
01:01:38,590 --> 01:01:40,510
Sing The La La Song.

1212
01:01:45,690 --> 01:01:46,770
Sing it!

1213
01:01:50,560 --> 01:01:52,230
This is good, right, Papa?

1214
01:01:52,320 --> 01:01:54,820
No! She's becoming one of them!

1215
01:01:54,940 --> 01:01:57,570
I have always wanted to do this!

1216
01:02:00,990 --> 01:02:02,330
We're losing her.

1217
01:02:02,540 --> 01:02:05,830
- Yes! Good one, Smurfette. - Your first cat zap.

1218
01:02:05,910 --> 01:02:08,500
Look at you. Look at you.

1219
01:02:10,250 --> 01:02:14,300
You truly are daddy's little girl.

1220
01:02:14,800 --> 01:02:16,760
- Smurfette! - No, Papa! Grouchy, grab him!

1221
01:02:16,970 --> 01:02:18,550
- No, Papa, he's gonna see you! - Get him down!

1222
01:02:18,760 --> 01:02:20,340
- Clumsy, help, help me get him down! - Papa, no!

1223
01:02:20,970 --> 01:02:22,680
Yeah!

1224
01:02:29,310 --> 01:02:31,650
No!

1225
01:02:33,860 --> 01:02:37,740
Take to the skies, lads. Free at last! Free at last!

1226
01:02:37,820 --> 01:02:40,320
- What are you, Martin Luther Wing? - That's it.

1227
01:02:40,490 --> 01:02:45,040
Joke it up, funny boy, but I am proud as a peacock to be a freedom flighter.

1228
01:02:45,660 --> 01:02:46,700
Oh, no.

1229
01:02:46,870 --> 01:02:48,660
What the... is that?

1230
01:02:50,370 --> 01:02:52,840
Hang on, Smurfs! Victor's on the way!

1231
01:02:53,000 --> 01:02:54,880
Pop your smurf-chutes.

1232
01:02:54,960 --> 01:02:56,210
The flying V!

1233
01:02:56,420 --> 01:02:58,260
Gotcha.

1234
01:02:59,130 --> 01:03:00,260
Okay, don't panic.

1235
01:03:00,340 --> 01:03:02,350
That is a lot of white meat.

1236
01:03:03,140 --> 01:03:04,560
Now panic!

1237
01:03:04,850 --> 01:03:06,390
Me no likey!

1238
01:03:12,230 --> 01:03:13,270
That was brilliant.

1239
01:03:13,940 --> 01:03:15,860
- He's naked, right? - Everyone okay?

1240
01:03:16,070 --> 01:03:19,070
Help me, somebody. Somebody please, let me out!

1241
01:03:21,030 --> 01:03:24,580
I have seen unspeakable things down there.

1242
01:03:25,200 --> 01:03:27,660
I have been scarred for life.

1243
01:03:29,210 --> 01:03:31,040
Where's Smurfette?

1244
01:03:33,040 --> 01:03:35,000
- She's... - Where's Smurfette?

1245
01:03:36,050 --> 01:03:38,760
We were too late.

1246
01:03:41,050 --> 01:03:42,050
Nice going.

1247
01:03:45,470 --> 01:03:49,770
Have fun, children. Just remember, be kind to each other.

1248
01:03:49,850 --> 01:03:52,060
Will you get away from me, you bumbling moron?

1249
01:03:52,140 --> 01:03:53,810
- Where are they? - What?

1250
01:03:53,900 --> 01:03:56,730
Smurfs were here? In this room? Why didn't you say so?

1251
01:03:56,900 --> 01:03:58,480
Right now!

1252
01:04:00,530 --> 01:04:01,570
She must not learn of this.

1253
01:04:01,950 --> 01:04:06,910
We must spirit her away from here and get that formula now.

1254
01:04:07,370 --> 01:04:10,410
Smurfette, my dear, are you ready to go celebrate?

1255
01:04:10,500 --> 01:04:12,160
- Yeah! - Come on, come on. This'll be fun.

1256
01:04:14,290 --> 01:04:15,420
We were this close to getting Smurfette back.

1257
01:04:15,500 --> 01:04:16,500
I know.

1258
01:04:16,590 --> 01:04:19,380
He distracted me at the worst possible moment, Grace.

1259
01:04:19,460 --> 01:04:21,260
I would have been in the elevator if it wasn't for him.

1260
01:04:21,340 --> 01:04:24,090
Okay, okay, use your indoor voice, and please, Patrick, just breathe.

1261
01:04:24,220 --> 01:04:25,850
I want him gone.

1262
01:04:25,930 --> 01:04:28,720
- He's your dad. - No, that's one thing he is not.

1263
01:04:28,810 --> 01:04:31,100
He's right, Grace. I'm not his father.

1264
01:04:32,480 --> 01:04:34,650
His real father left and started a new family.

1265
01:04:35,770 --> 01:04:37,400
He's been chewed up about it ever since.

1266
01:04:38,230 --> 01:04:40,150
- Excuse me? - As well you might.

1267
01:04:40,360 --> 01:04:43,820
But I can't take the brunt of it anymore.

1268
01:04:44,030 --> 01:04:47,530
Hey, I never asked for you to come barging into my life, okay?

1269
01:04:47,780 --> 01:04:51,540
I didn't ask you to marry my mother or take away Zeus.

1270
01:04:51,870 --> 01:04:54,080
Zeus? The pigeon?

1271
01:04:54,790 --> 01:04:56,250
The parrot.

1272
01:04:56,330 --> 01:04:57,920
My parrot.

1273
01:04:58,000 --> 01:05:01,090
Taken away because you were allergic.

1274
01:05:04,430 --> 01:05:06,140
I was not allergic to that bird, Patrick.

1275
01:05:06,340 --> 01:05:07,470
Yes, you were.

1276
01:05:08,300 --> 01:05:10,510
No, I wasn't.

1277
01:05:10,600 --> 01:05:11,640
You were.

1278
01:05:12,310 --> 01:05:13,640
What?

1279
01:05:13,850 --> 01:05:17,020
It got so bad, every day, you were wheezing, coughing.

1280
01:05:17,400 --> 01:05:19,570
Your mother and I both knew that it would break your heart

1281
01:05:19,650 --> 01:05:22,190
to think the bird had to go away because of you.

1282
01:05:22,490 --> 01:05:24,740
You already blamed yourself for your dad.

1283
01:05:24,820 --> 01:05:26,070
So I took the heat.

1284
01:05:26,950 --> 01:05:30,490
That's a lie. What are you... I'm not allergic to birds.

1285
01:05:31,160 --> 01:05:32,910
Okay, tell you what.

1286
01:05:33,500 --> 01:05:34,500
Sniff my feathers.

1287
01:05:34,870 --> 01:05:37,210
- I'm not going to... - Come on, sniff them.

1288
01:05:43,920 --> 01:05:45,010
Truth itches, doesn't it?

1289
01:05:49,890 --> 01:05:51,970
Listen to me, Patrick.

1290
01:05:52,060 --> 01:05:54,350
I loved your mother with all my heart.

1291
01:05:54,520 --> 01:05:57,810
I took care of Jeannette, and I made her happy.

1292
01:05:58,060 --> 01:06:00,770
I also chose to love you as my own.

1293
01:06:00,860 --> 01:06:02,360
Now, I didn't have to do that.

1294
01:06:02,440 --> 01:06:07,740
But you were this little kid, no father, no hope in his eyes, a big hole in his heart,

1295
01:06:07,820 --> 01:06:09,370
so I gave you everything I could.

1296
01:06:10,070 --> 01:06:11,910
But I'm done, you know?

1297
01:06:11,990 --> 01:06:14,500
You don't want it, that's fine.

1298
01:06:15,000 --> 01:06:17,000
My last word of advice to you is this...

1299
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:19,170
Will you grow up?

1300
01:06:19,830 --> 01:06:22,710
Stop blaming everyone else for your pain.

1301
01:06:22,880 --> 01:06:24,000
And whatever you do,

1302
01:06:24,090 --> 01:06:27,720
don't teach that beautiful son of yours that love is conditional,

1303
01:06:27,760 --> 01:06:29,680
because it is not.

1304
01:06:31,550 --> 01:06:33,390
Good bye, Grace.

1305
01:06:38,190 --> 01:06:40,060
Bye-bye, Blue.

1306
01:06:49,320 --> 01:06:51,320
Grandpa Vicster.

1307
01:06:55,160 --> 01:06:56,160
Bye.

1308
01:06:59,790 --> 01:07:01,540
Goodbye, Patrick Winslow.

1309
01:07:11,800 --> 01:07:14,430
Look at that big wheel.

1310
01:07:14,510 --> 01:07:17,310
Come. Come along, my dear.

1311
01:07:17,600 --> 01:07:20,690
So this is why they call it the City of Light.

1312
01:07:21,770 --> 01:07:23,400
There's a lot of people.

1313
01:07:23,650 --> 01:07:25,520
Yes, well...

1314
01:07:25,610 --> 01:07:28,860
I prefer to call them "worshippers."

1315
01:07:28,940 --> 01:07:30,360
"Worshippers."

1316
01:07:31,160 --> 01:07:32,950
Alakakneel!

1317
01:07:34,280 --> 01:07:37,120
Bow. Kneel.

1318
01:07:38,080 --> 01:07:39,410
Hackus.

1319
01:07:39,500 --> 01:07:41,540
- Shall we? - Let's go.

1320
01:07:41,620 --> 01:07:45,960
Don't worry. Everyone likes it. He's a celebrity. Come on.

1321
01:07:46,090 --> 01:07:47,300
Okay.

1322
01:07:47,800 --> 01:07:49,760
Yes, hello. It's me.

1323
01:07:49,880 --> 01:07:52,430
- These are my children. - Hi.

1324
01:07:52,510 --> 01:07:54,090
- Who's that? - That's my brother.

1325
01:07:54,180 --> 01:07:55,260
Hi. I'm Hackus.

1326
01:07:55,760 --> 01:07:57,930
Look at that. It's a magical creature.

1327
01:07:58,310 --> 01:07:59,770
Hi.

1328
01:07:59,850 --> 01:08:01,190
It's my birthday.

1329
01:08:01,770 --> 01:08:02,810
Thank you.

1330
01:08:02,900 --> 01:08:05,110
- I have a FASTPASS. - Yeah, FASTPASS.

1331
01:08:06,150 --> 01:08:07,610
Monsieur Gargamel!

1332
01:08:08,280 --> 01:08:10,490
Thank you for keeping our seats warm. Goodbye.

1333
01:08:10,610 --> 01:08:11,650
Bye-bye!

1334
01:08:11,780 --> 01:08:14,820
Come along, children. Right this way.

1335
01:08:15,070 --> 01:08:17,990
Monsieur Gargamel! Monsieur Gargamel!

1336
01:08:19,500 --> 01:08:20,910
Let's go!

1337
01:08:21,000 --> 01:08:22,250
- Father. - Not now.

1338
01:08:22,330 --> 01:08:23,750
It's feeding time soon.

1339
01:08:23,830 --> 01:08:25,750
- Not now! - But...

1340
01:08:27,920 --> 01:08:29,000
Here we are.

1341
01:08:30,170 --> 01:08:33,760
- Our fun is just beginning, eh? - Yeah.

1342
01:08:34,550 --> 01:08:37,140
Alakazelevate!

1343
01:08:43,020 --> 01:08:45,560
But isn't this lovely, my dear?

1344
01:08:45,940 --> 01:08:47,820
And just think,

1345
01:08:47,900 --> 01:08:52,280
with your secret formula and my incredible magic,

1346
01:08:52,360 --> 01:08:56,370
there's absolutely nothing that we cannot do.

1347
01:08:57,700 --> 01:08:59,280
Yeah.

1348
01:08:59,370 --> 01:09:02,500
Think of all the fun we could have, Smurfette.

1349
01:09:07,840 --> 01:09:09,250
Okay.

1350
01:09:09,340 --> 01:09:12,800
Then why are we going so slow?

1351
01:09:32,480 --> 01:09:34,820
- Look out! - Yeah!

1352
01:09:34,900 --> 01:09:36,490
Isn't this fun?

1353
01:09:36,570 --> 01:09:38,160
Decidedly not!

1354
01:09:48,540 --> 01:09:52,250
Best ride ever! Smurfette's fun, huh?

1355
01:09:58,800 --> 01:10:00,470
Incoming!

1356
01:10:00,550 --> 01:10:03,270
Look out! Coming through!

1357
01:10:06,440 --> 01:10:07,730
Sorry!

1358
01:10:24,450 --> 01:10:26,120
I must have failed her.

1359
01:10:27,580 --> 01:10:30,790
Sorry. I was looking for a place to think.

1360
01:10:30,960 --> 01:10:33,550
No, no, no, no. It's okay.

1361
01:10:33,630 --> 01:10:36,300
I was doing a little thinking myself.

1362
01:10:39,930 --> 01:10:42,930
Master Winslow, it's hard for me,

1363
01:10:43,100 --> 01:10:46,430
but, well, can I ask you some advice?

1364
01:10:46,640 --> 01:10:48,480
I mean, papa to Papa.

1365
01:10:49,600 --> 01:10:51,310
It's about Smurfette.

1366
01:10:52,150 --> 01:10:53,820
I don't know what to do.

1367
01:10:53,980 --> 01:10:56,110
I turned her blue.

1368
01:10:56,190 --> 01:10:58,990
I taught her love and kindness.

1369
01:10:59,110 --> 01:11:01,990
But the truth is, Gargamel made her.

1370
01:11:02,070 --> 01:11:06,120
She's only a Smurf as long as she chooses to be.

1371
01:11:06,200 --> 01:11:08,540
But what if she doesn't?

1372
01:11:10,210 --> 01:11:12,420
What if she chooses him?

1373
01:11:12,500 --> 01:11:14,670
We could lose her.

1374
01:11:14,750 --> 01:11:16,670
We may have already.

1375
01:11:18,590 --> 01:11:20,300
I haven't done enough.

1376
01:11:20,380 --> 01:11:21,760
Are you kidding?

1377
01:11:21,930 --> 01:11:24,300
Gargamel just made her, but you,

1378
01:11:24,390 --> 01:11:25,760
you made her what she is.

1379
01:11:25,850 --> 01:11:28,730
You stepped in and loved her as your very own.

1380
01:11:29,020 --> 01:11:31,020
No one asked you to, you just did.

1381
01:11:31,350 --> 01:11:33,610
Because you knew she needed that.

1382
01:11:33,690 --> 01:11:35,820
And that's a...

1383
01:11:38,360 --> 01:11:41,910
That's a pretty special kind of love.

1384
01:11:44,530 --> 01:11:46,700
She's way too smart not to see that.

1385
01:11:49,370 --> 01:11:50,960
You're right.

1386
01:11:51,040 --> 01:11:53,710
We didn't believe in her because she changed.

1387
01:11:53,790 --> 01:11:56,170
She changed because we believed in her.

1388
01:11:57,960 --> 01:11:59,630
Thank you, Master Winslow.

1389
01:11:59,720 --> 01:12:03,050
That was exactly what I needed to hear.

1390
01:12:11,890 --> 01:12:13,400
Me, too.

1391
01:12:15,610 --> 01:12:17,270
Just a few more bubbles.

1392
01:12:17,520 --> 01:12:18,900
How's that?

1393
01:12:18,980 --> 01:12:22,240
Sweet Smurf in Heaven, what have you eaten?

1394
01:12:22,400 --> 01:12:25,740
It's okay. Every time a Smurf toots, someone smiles.

1395
01:12:26,580 --> 01:12:27,990
- Let's go, Smurfs. - Where?

1396
01:12:28,080 --> 01:12:29,240
We're getting Smurfette.

1397
01:12:29,410 --> 01:12:31,160
But you saw her, Papa.

1398
01:12:31,750 --> 01:12:33,170
She's one of them now.

1399
01:12:33,250 --> 01:12:35,000
- A horse whisperer? - No!

1400
01:12:35,080 --> 01:12:37,040
- A French Socialist? - No!

1401
01:12:37,130 --> 01:12:38,250
A Flying Wallenda!

1402
01:12:38,340 --> 01:12:40,130
No, she's with Gargamel. Keep up.

1403
01:12:40,340 --> 01:12:42,010
I don't care what we saw.

1404
01:12:42,090 --> 01:12:44,430
You never give up on family.

1405
01:12:44,510 --> 01:12:46,430
Yeah, Papa's right.

1406
01:12:46,510 --> 01:12:48,810
Who are you, and what have you done with Grouchy?

1407
01:12:48,890 --> 01:12:51,020
Hey, I'm Positive, remember?

1408
01:12:51,600 --> 01:12:54,140
All right, Smurfs. Let's get smurfing.

1409
01:12:55,100 --> 01:12:57,270
Master Winslow, you coming with us?

1410
01:12:57,440 --> 01:12:58,940
Is a Smurf's butt blue?

1411
01:13:01,190 --> 01:13:02,440
You tell me.

1412
01:13:02,900 --> 01:13:04,030
Grouchy.

1413
01:13:04,320 --> 01:13:07,030
- Put it away. - Anybody else?

1414
01:13:07,660 --> 01:13:09,740
Okay, then. Out of the tub with you.

1415
01:13:09,830 --> 01:13:10,910
- We've got work to do. - Hey.

1416
01:13:10,990 --> 01:13:13,120
Let's smurf this mushroom stand. Let's roll.

1417
01:13:13,210 --> 01:13:15,370
Yeah, guys, let's do this.

1418
01:13:24,340 --> 01:13:25,430
Victor? Hey.

1419
01:13:54,160 --> 01:13:56,040
Okay, Master Winslow, we'll split up here.

1420
01:13:56,210 --> 01:13:58,290
All right. I'll find the electrical room and cut the power.

1421
01:13:58,500 --> 01:13:59,500
And we'll find Smurfette.

1422
01:13:59,580 --> 01:14:01,670
And we'll all look fabulous doing it.

1423
01:14:02,050 --> 01:14:03,340
Oh, come on.

1424
01:14:03,420 --> 01:14:05,380
Team building. Hello!

1425
01:14:05,550 --> 01:14:08,010
All right, see you inside. Good luck.

1426
01:14:08,180 --> 01:14:10,010
- Come on, guys. - lnto the belly of the beast.

1427
01:14:12,350 --> 01:14:14,640
Why are we coming down here, Father?

1428
01:14:14,730 --> 01:14:18,690
Well, we are celebrating your long-lost sister's birthday.

1429
01:14:18,770 --> 01:14:19,770
Really?

1430
01:14:19,860 --> 01:14:22,270
Can't very well end the festivities without

1431
01:14:23,900 --> 01:14:25,190
a cake.

1432
01:14:26,320 --> 01:14:29,700
I made you your favourite, my dear. Blue velvet.

1433
01:14:31,370 --> 01:14:32,490
Cake.

1434
01:14:33,580 --> 01:14:36,620
Go ahead. Go ahead. Make a wish, my dear.

1435
01:14:36,710 --> 01:14:41,250
Anything your tiny little heart can dream of, and it is yours.

1436
01:14:41,590 --> 01:14:43,050
Anything?

1437
01:14:43,130 --> 01:14:44,420
But of course.

1438
01:14:45,210 --> 01:14:46,880
Yes, well, within reason.

1439
01:14:46,970 --> 01:14:51,220
I'm afraid we're on a bit of an essence budget around here lately.

1440
01:14:51,300 --> 01:14:54,720
That's why we need the formula, you see.

1441
01:15:01,480 --> 01:15:03,230
There she is.

1442
01:15:03,400 --> 01:15:05,280
Is that a birthday cake?

1443
01:15:05,360 --> 01:15:07,240
We had a birthday cake for her, too.

1444
01:15:07,400 --> 01:15:09,820
She just never saw it.

1445
01:15:09,910 --> 01:15:12,870
They look like a happy family.

1446
01:15:12,950 --> 01:15:15,290
She's not going to give him the formula, is she, Papa?

1447
01:15:15,370 --> 01:15:18,960
If she does, it would mean the end of all Smurf kind.

1448
01:15:20,580 --> 01:15:22,670
Wait. Even the handsome ones?

1449
01:15:22,790 --> 01:15:24,750
- Yeah. - Vanity, you come with me.

1450
01:15:24,840 --> 01:15:27,090
Clumsy and Grouchy, go meet Master Winslow.

1451
01:15:38,390 --> 01:15:40,190
Victor, what are you doing here?

1452
01:15:40,270 --> 01:15:41,390
Grace called me.

1453
01:15:41,520 --> 01:15:43,610
She said you might need a hand.

1454
01:15:46,480 --> 01:15:48,320
No, no. Victor, wait.

1455
01:15:49,900 --> 01:15:51,910
As usual, Grace is right.

1456
01:15:52,860 --> 01:15:53,910
I could use some help.

1457
01:15:54,490 --> 01:15:57,660
Well, for starters, you might try lifting the sewer cover.

1458
01:15:57,740 --> 01:15:59,160
Unless you're planning on fixing the phone lines?

1459
01:16:04,840 --> 01:16:06,960
Smurfette, the formula?

1460
01:16:07,050 --> 01:16:08,920
Take all the time you need, my dear.

1461
01:16:09,090 --> 01:16:10,720
As long as it's very, very soon.

1462
01:16:10,880 --> 01:16:13,720
Then we can all be blue. Together.

1463
01:16:13,840 --> 01:16:17,100
Hackus blue. Hackus blue.

1464
01:16:17,640 --> 01:16:19,220
You see? They want to be blue,

1465
01:16:19,640 --> 01:16:21,480
just like their big sister.

1466
01:16:21,980 --> 01:16:24,650
Then we could be a real family.

1467
01:16:29,070 --> 01:16:30,990
This is something.

1468
01:16:31,070 --> 01:16:35,370
A sacred gift entrusted to me.

1469
01:16:38,330 --> 01:16:39,830
I'm sorry.

1470
01:16:41,120 --> 01:16:42,710
I just, I...

1471
01:16:44,210 --> 01:16:45,500
I can't.

1472
01:16:48,340 --> 01:16:50,920
What do you mean, you can't?

1473
01:16:51,010 --> 01:16:52,340
I've given you everything.

1474
01:16:52,970 --> 01:16:54,550
Kindness, presents,

1475
01:16:54,720 --> 01:16:57,760
a cake with no poison. It's been horrible!

1476
01:16:57,850 --> 01:17:00,560
Now, I have had just about enough of this, young lady.

1477
01:17:00,640 --> 01:17:03,440
You are going to give me what I want right now!

1478
01:17:03,520 --> 01:17:04,850
- The formula! - No!

1479
01:17:04,940 --> 01:17:05,940
Yes!

1480
01:17:06,020 --> 01:17:07,360
- Father? - What, what, what?

1481
01:17:09,650 --> 01:17:12,320
Hackus dizzy.

1482
01:17:12,400 --> 01:17:13,990
What's happening to them?

1483
01:17:14,150 --> 01:17:15,410
So dizzy.

1484
01:17:15,490 --> 01:17:18,950
Don't tell me you actually care for these pathetic creatures.

1485
01:17:19,030 --> 01:17:20,290
How sad for you.

1486
01:17:22,040 --> 01:17:26,210
And how absolutely perfect for me.

1487
01:17:26,710 --> 01:17:27,960
It looks like the power lines run this way.

1488
01:17:28,040 --> 01:17:29,790
Let's go! Let's go! We got to get her out of there!

1489
01:17:29,880 --> 01:17:31,340
All right, let's do this!

1490
01:17:31,500 --> 01:17:33,630
This way, Vanity. Through this pipe.

1491
01:17:33,720 --> 01:17:36,970
We have to save her! This could be my moment!

1492
01:17:38,850 --> 01:17:42,810
I'm so sorry, my dear. I thought you knew.

1493
01:17:42,890 --> 01:17:46,230
Without essence, they cannot live.

1494
01:17:47,400 --> 01:17:48,770
- Father. - No.

1495
01:17:48,940 --> 01:17:50,110
Please.

1496
01:17:50,190 --> 01:17:51,820
No. Vexy.

1497
01:17:55,400 --> 01:17:57,490
So dizzy.

1498
01:17:58,070 --> 01:18:00,280
- Hackus. - Smurfette.

1499
01:18:00,910 --> 01:18:02,910
Give them what you have! Take some from me.

1500
01:18:03,040 --> 01:18:04,040
Take some!

1501
01:18:05,080 --> 01:18:06,120
Please!

1502
01:18:06,210 --> 01:18:08,750
What's the point? You won't give me the formula,

1503
01:18:08,830 --> 01:18:12,670
so, well, I might as well just let them go.

1504
01:18:13,050 --> 01:18:14,130
Vexy.

1505
01:18:15,550 --> 01:18:18,260
You mean you'd let them die?

1506
01:18:19,550 --> 01:18:21,260
I can always make others.

1507
01:18:21,390 --> 01:18:25,180
Besides, I am not the one letting them die.

1508
01:18:25,600 --> 01:18:26,690
You are.

1509
01:18:29,100 --> 01:18:31,060
Okay. Okay.

1510
01:18:31,440 --> 01:18:34,360
I'll give it to you. Just feed them.

1511
01:18:35,570 --> 01:18:37,450
The formula first.

1512
01:18:37,650 --> 01:18:40,280
Feed them. Feed them!

1513
01:18:40,450 --> 01:18:41,910
Quickly. We have to get in there.

1514
01:18:41,990 --> 01:18:44,120
- Dead end! - It's locked!

1515
01:18:45,660 --> 01:18:49,120
The formu-la-la-la-la-la-la.

1516
01:18:51,630 --> 01:18:53,130
One hopeful thought.

1517
01:18:54,340 --> 01:18:56,420
A dab of royal jelly.

1518
01:18:57,840 --> 01:18:59,130
Mimosa pollen.

1519
01:18:59,220 --> 01:19:00,260
Smurfette.

1520
01:19:00,340 --> 01:19:02,600
- Smurfette! - Yes, good girl.

1521
01:19:02,800 --> 01:19:04,720
I can hear them, but I can't see them.

1522
01:19:04,810 --> 01:19:06,930
Wait! I know.

1523
01:19:07,020 --> 01:19:08,060
Papa, look.

1524
01:19:08,230 --> 01:19:09,690
- And a drop of mink oil. - I knew it.

1525
01:19:09,770 --> 01:19:12,060
Is she giving him the formula?

1526
01:19:12,150 --> 01:19:13,520
- Oh, no. - Smurfette.

1527
01:19:13,610 --> 01:19:14,650
Help me get this open.

1528
01:19:15,150 --> 01:19:17,780
And you must say one loving truth.

1529
01:19:18,400 --> 01:19:20,160
- Of course. - There.

1530
01:19:20,280 --> 01:19:22,410
That's the formula Papa used.

1531
01:19:22,490 --> 01:19:24,160
Now, feed them! Please!

1532
01:19:24,240 --> 01:19:25,330
First, we'll see if this works, huh?

1533
01:19:27,330 --> 01:19:28,540
Hurry!

1534
01:19:29,710 --> 01:19:30,750
- Come on. - Here we are.

1535
01:19:30,830 --> 01:19:32,170
Let's go! Let's go!

1536
01:19:33,840 --> 01:19:35,460
Pull, Patrick. Put your back into it.

1537
01:19:35,710 --> 01:19:38,130
- Come on! - Hey, there's an opening down here.

1538
01:19:38,340 --> 01:19:40,880
- Come on, Positive. - Yeah, let's shut 'em down.

1539
01:19:41,300 --> 01:19:43,600
One loving truth.

1540
01:19:43,680 --> 01:19:45,350
I hope this works.

1541
01:20:29,220 --> 01:20:30,520
Hackus.

1542
01:20:32,140 --> 01:20:35,730
- Smurfette. Thank you. - Vexy!

1543
01:20:35,900 --> 01:20:39,070
Oh, my Smurf, it worked.

1544
01:20:39,230 --> 01:20:40,570
- Hackus! - Hackus blue!

1545
01:20:40,650 --> 01:20:42,570
Hackus.

1546
01:20:42,700 --> 01:20:44,410
Hackus is blue!

1547
01:20:44,530 --> 01:20:46,990
We're blue! We're Smurfs!

1548
01:20:47,120 --> 01:20:49,330
It worked. All the world is mine!

1549
01:20:49,660 --> 01:20:52,410
- I can make my own Smurfs! - No!

1550
01:20:53,920 --> 01:20:56,580
We've been betrayed.

1551
01:20:57,090 --> 01:20:59,300
Finally, finally.

1552
01:20:59,380 --> 01:21:01,260
You're a real boy.

1553
01:21:01,420 --> 01:21:02,420
I'm blue.

1554
01:21:02,590 --> 01:21:04,430
Now into the machine with all of you.

1555
01:21:04,630 --> 01:21:05,680
Father, no.

1556
01:21:06,640 --> 01:21:10,600
- No cage for Hackus. No cage for Hackus. - All right, all right.

1557
01:21:11,220 --> 01:21:13,100
- In you go. - No cage for Hackus!

1558
01:21:13,180 --> 01:21:15,270
- Everybody gets their own room. - Please!

1559
01:21:15,690 --> 01:21:18,730
- I failed her, Vanity. - Papa, wait.

1560
01:21:19,440 --> 01:21:21,320
I think I can reach that pin.

1561
01:21:21,400 --> 01:21:22,900
Good idea, Vanity.

1562
01:21:22,990 --> 01:21:24,360
Come on, come on.

1563
01:21:25,280 --> 01:21:26,660
Father, please.

1564
01:21:26,740 --> 01:21:28,240
Now, don't go anywhere.

1565
01:21:30,580 --> 01:21:33,790
You face leaking.

1566
01:21:35,120 --> 01:21:37,290
Hackus leaking.

1567
01:21:38,590 --> 01:21:41,210
Hackus leaking.

1568
01:21:41,300 --> 01:21:46,090
You sacrificed everything just to save us.

1569
01:21:46,680 --> 01:21:48,140
I had to.

1570
01:21:48,720 --> 01:21:49,890
I care about you.

1571
01:21:51,970 --> 01:21:53,520
We're family.

1572
01:21:54,680 --> 01:21:56,900
No like leaking.

1573
01:21:56,980 --> 01:21:58,730
Hackus like blue.

1574
01:21:58,900 --> 01:22:01,070
What a sickening scene.

1575
01:22:01,150 --> 01:22:03,820
I'd be completely nauseated if this weren't

1576
01:22:04,030 --> 01:22:06,910
the happiest moment of my life!

1577
01:22:07,070 --> 01:22:09,070
- Try the lever, the big one. - Get on my shoulders.

1578
01:22:09,370 --> 01:22:10,830
Hurry, lads.

1579
01:22:10,910 --> 01:22:11,950
Which way do I go?

1580
01:22:12,040 --> 01:22:13,950
Try negative. That might shut it off.

1581
01:22:14,040 --> 01:22:16,870
Negative? Nah. I'm all about positive.

1582
01:22:20,170 --> 01:22:21,210
There.

1583
01:22:21,290 --> 01:22:25,260
One small step for a wizard,

1584
01:22:25,340 --> 01:22:28,340
one giant leap for... What?

1585
01:22:29,590 --> 01:22:30,680
Positive!

1586
01:22:31,180 --> 01:22:33,310
Too much smurf berry cobbler.

1587
01:22:33,600 --> 01:22:34,600
Grouchy!

1588
01:22:34,850 --> 01:22:37,770
Yes, I said you could press the button, didn't I?

1589
01:22:40,230 --> 01:22:42,110
Grouchy!

1590
01:22:42,270 --> 01:22:44,360
I lied. One giant leap for me!

1591
01:22:49,280 --> 01:22:50,740
Just got fried.

1592
01:22:50,820 --> 01:22:53,200
Hard to put a positive spin on that.

1593
01:22:58,370 --> 01:22:59,540
Son of a Smurf!

1594
01:22:59,710 --> 01:23:00,710
Hurry, Vanity.

1595
01:23:00,790 --> 01:23:04,050
Narcissism is about to save the day.

1596
01:23:04,550 --> 01:23:05,670
- Got it! - Smurftastic work.

1597
01:23:05,800 --> 01:23:07,010
- I knew it. - Now go.

1598
01:23:07,090 --> 01:23:08,550
- What? - Go!

1599
01:23:08,720 --> 01:23:09,930
Come, Azrael!

1600
01:23:10,010 --> 01:23:14,310
Apparently, we must harness the power of the skies one final time.

1601
01:23:14,390 --> 01:23:15,810
Why does this have to be so Les Misérables?

1602
01:23:15,890 --> 01:23:18,430
- Let's go. - Look at me, all rough-and-tumble.

1603
01:23:18,520 --> 01:23:20,480
I'm like Commando Smurf.

1604
01:23:20,560 --> 01:23:21,770
Hooah!

1605
01:23:22,810 --> 01:23:25,360
You are right. Commandos are quiet and stealthy.

1606
01:23:25,570 --> 01:23:26,940
Hooah!

1607
01:23:27,030 --> 01:23:28,490
- There she is! - Smurfette.

1608
01:23:29,570 --> 01:23:30,820
Santa!

1609
01:23:31,280 --> 01:23:34,280
Papa? You... You came for me.

1610
01:23:34,450 --> 01:23:37,700
Well, of course we came for you. You're my daughter.

1611
01:23:37,870 --> 01:23:39,580
Was there ever a question?

1612
01:23:39,790 --> 01:23:41,370
- No, it's locked. - Go on through.

1613
01:23:41,580 --> 01:23:42,670
- We'll find another way. - Okay.

1614
01:23:42,750 --> 01:23:45,210
We'll see you in there, Master Winslow. Hurry!

1615
01:23:48,630 --> 01:23:49,880
Here.

1616
01:23:50,550 --> 01:23:51,840
Hold this!

1617
01:24:08,650 --> 01:24:09,860
Papa.

1618
01:24:09,940 --> 01:24:12,110
Oh, my dear.

1619
01:24:12,780 --> 01:24:16,450
Papa, I gave Gargamel the formula.

1620
01:24:16,660 --> 01:24:18,200
But she saved our lives.

1621
01:24:18,370 --> 01:24:20,830
Hackus live! Hackus live!

1622
01:24:20,910 --> 01:24:23,790
Papa, I let you down.

1623
01:24:24,630 --> 01:24:27,050
I betrayed the Smurfs.

1624
01:24:27,130 --> 01:24:28,630
I'm so sorry.

1625
01:24:28,840 --> 01:24:33,720
Smurfette, life is the most precious thing to protect.

1626
01:24:33,800 --> 01:24:35,890
I'm very proud of you.

1627
01:24:35,970 --> 01:24:37,930
You... You are?

1628
01:24:38,140 --> 01:24:41,020
Seriously? No spanking? No smack to the knuckles?

1629
01:24:41,100 --> 01:24:43,140
You forgive her, just like that?

1630
01:24:43,390 --> 01:24:46,730
Of course. We rise to the amount of love we're shown,

1631
01:24:46,810 --> 01:24:50,110
and we sink only when that love stops.

1632
01:24:50,190 --> 01:24:53,860
Hackus leaking again. Leaking again!

1633
01:24:54,280 --> 01:24:55,660
Hey, you found Smurfette!

1634
01:24:56,320 --> 01:24:57,530
Hello.

1635
01:24:58,580 --> 01:24:59,620
Hi.

1636
01:25:01,540 --> 01:25:02,750
Oh, no, we don't have much time.

1637
01:25:02,960 --> 01:25:06,210
Let's just get the formula back and get out of here. Hooah!

1638
01:25:06,330 --> 01:25:07,920
Wait! What about them?

1639
01:25:08,090 --> 01:25:10,050
What about them? They kidnapped you.

1640
01:25:10,130 --> 01:25:11,420
Yeah, they're Gargamel's.

1641
01:25:11,510 --> 01:25:16,050
So was I, but Papa never gave up on me.

1642
01:25:16,140 --> 01:25:18,510
So I'm not about to give up on them.

1643
01:25:19,140 --> 01:25:21,470
And you thought you weren't a real Smurf.

1644
01:25:22,770 --> 01:25:24,350
- Get them out, quickly. - Right, Papa.

1645
01:25:24,440 --> 01:25:26,020
Free Hackus!

1646
01:25:26,190 --> 01:25:28,610
And then there were seven, eh?

1647
01:25:29,820 --> 01:25:31,150
Hello, kitty.

1648
01:25:31,360 --> 01:25:33,860
Welcome to the party, Papa!

1649
01:25:35,360 --> 01:25:37,820
Look at all this essence.

1650
01:25:40,490 --> 01:25:43,620
I love your work. Really, all of you.

1651
01:25:43,710 --> 01:25:46,540
In particular, your Blue Period.

1652
01:25:47,210 --> 01:25:50,040
My whole body is scrunching!

1653
01:25:50,250 --> 01:25:52,460
That's enough, Gargamel.

1654
01:25:52,550 --> 01:25:53,970
You have enough.

1655
01:25:54,050 --> 01:25:58,800
Yes, yes, but you see, Papa, I want more than enough!

1656
01:26:01,470 --> 01:26:05,060
After all, I have to be able to power this!

1657
01:26:06,890 --> 01:26:10,150
I call her La Wanda.

1658
01:26:11,860 --> 01:26:13,530
You get it? Because it's a wand.

1659
01:26:13,610 --> 01:26:15,400
So I called it La... It's very funny.

1660
01:26:15,490 --> 01:26:19,320
If you weren't in excruciating pain, you'd be laughing hysterically, believe me.

1661
01:26:23,700 --> 01:26:27,460
Whatever will I do with all of this power?

1662
01:26:29,420 --> 01:26:30,590
That's right.

1663
01:26:30,670 --> 01:26:34,010
I'm going to rule the entire world!

1664
01:26:34,260 --> 01:26:35,590
No.

1665
01:26:36,300 --> 01:26:37,510
And, Papa,

1666
01:26:37,590 --> 01:26:40,470
I want you to know that as my first official act,

1667
01:26:40,550 --> 01:26:42,370
I'm going to create a portal

1668
01:26:42,820 --> 01:26:47,310
all the way from Smurf Village right here to my Smurfalator,

1669
01:26:47,390 --> 01:26:51,730
so you get to be with all of your little smurfy friends.

1670
01:26:53,650 --> 01:26:55,360
Forever!

1671
01:26:55,440 --> 01:26:56,570
I don't think so, Gargamel.

1672
01:27:00,740 --> 01:27:01,820
Hit it again.

1673
01:27:02,030 --> 01:27:03,120
- Give it to me. - Hurry.

1674
01:27:04,370 --> 01:27:06,200
Hurry, he's going for his wand.

1675
01:27:07,120 --> 01:27:09,920
- Just break it already! - I'm too beautiful to die!

1676
01:27:10,920 --> 01:27:13,840
For the love of Smurf, use the pointy end!

1677
01:27:13,920 --> 01:27:16,090
Don't just stand there yelling at me! Attack!

1678
01:27:17,300 --> 01:27:18,340
Yes!

1679
01:27:25,010 --> 01:27:26,310
Alaka...

1680
01:28:14,020 --> 01:28:15,770
Hackus real boy.

1681
01:28:16,360 --> 01:28:18,360
Thrown to the curb again.

1682
01:28:18,440 --> 01:28:20,190
Careful, Clumsy!

1683
01:28:20,280 --> 01:28:21,990
- Every time! - Sorry.

1684
01:28:22,150 --> 01:28:23,200
Really?

1685
01:28:23,280 --> 01:28:24,450
High fours!

1686
01:28:35,290 --> 01:28:36,500
Is everyone all right?

1687
01:28:36,710 --> 01:28:38,750
All smurfy and accounted for.

1688
01:28:39,010 --> 01:28:41,090
- Patrick! - Daddy!

1689
01:28:41,170 --> 01:28:42,760
- Hey. - Hey, Grace!

1690
01:28:42,840 --> 01:28:44,220
Hey.

1691
01:28:45,300 --> 01:28:46,470
We did it!

1692
01:28:46,550 --> 01:28:48,100
Oh, Grace!

1693
01:28:48,180 --> 01:28:49,270
Smurfette.

1694
01:28:49,430 --> 01:28:50,560
I've missed you.

1695
01:28:51,310 --> 01:28:53,060
I was so worried about you.

1696
01:28:53,230 --> 01:28:56,310
Grace, this is Vexy, my other sister.

1697
01:28:57,520 --> 01:28:59,780
Well, I guess that makes you my sister, too.

1698
01:29:01,610 --> 01:29:03,070
Are you okay?

1699
01:29:05,620 --> 01:29:07,870
Is this what happy feels like?

1700
01:29:08,740 --> 01:29:11,000
Hello, pretty lady! I'm pretty, too!

1701
01:29:11,080 --> 01:29:13,620
And this is Hackus, my brother.

1702
01:29:13,710 --> 01:29:14,750
Hackus!

1703
01:29:14,870 --> 01:29:16,750
Hackus, this is Grace and Patrick.

1704
01:29:17,130 --> 01:29:19,460
- Hello! - And... Your baby?

1705
01:29:19,630 --> 01:29:20,920
This is Blue.

1706
01:29:21,420 --> 01:29:22,970
You did good, Grace.

1707
01:29:23,050 --> 01:29:24,840
He's blue-tiful.

1708
01:29:25,430 --> 01:29:26,970
Who this? Who this?

1709
01:29:27,050 --> 01:29:28,550
That's Victor.

1710
01:29:28,720 --> 01:29:29,760
He's...

1711
01:29:29,890 --> 01:29:30,890
He's my dad.

1712
01:29:32,270 --> 01:29:34,730
And Blue's pretty fantastic grandpa.

1713
01:29:40,650 --> 01:29:42,280
Daddy and Vicster!

1714
01:29:44,280 --> 01:29:46,490
Okay. I got it.

1715
01:29:46,740 --> 01:29:48,280
I'm really proud of you, Patrick Winslow.

1716
01:29:48,450 --> 01:29:50,700
Hyphen-Doyle.

1717
01:29:51,450 --> 01:29:52,870
Hyphen-Smurf.

1718
01:29:53,660 --> 01:29:56,120
Yeah, guys! Smurf pound.

1719
01:29:56,210 --> 01:29:58,750
- Vanity? - Great job! Great job!

1720
01:29:58,830 --> 01:30:00,540
- Positive? - Hey, get that thing out of here!

1721
01:30:00,630 --> 01:30:01,920
I'm not pounding anything!

1722
01:30:02,000 --> 01:30:05,340
I'm Grouchy, and I got a lot of pent-up anger to vent!

1723
01:30:05,720 --> 01:30:07,590
Wow, that feels good.

1724
01:30:07,680 --> 01:30:08,840
I'm back!

1725
01:30:09,260 --> 01:30:10,930
And so am I!

1726
01:30:11,470 --> 01:30:12,560
Perfect.

1727
01:30:12,720 --> 01:30:14,350
I think most of you know La Wanda...

1728
01:30:14,430 --> 01:30:17,730
- Unfortunately. - ...which is a hilarious play on words.

1729
01:30:18,730 --> 01:30:22,570
- Smurfette. - Say hello to my enormous friend!

1730
01:30:22,860 --> 01:30:25,280
I don't think so, Gargamel!

1731
01:30:29,700 --> 01:30:30,830
Yeah!

1732
01:30:32,120 --> 01:30:34,620
Wanda! No, La Wanda, no!

1733
01:30:34,700 --> 01:30:37,500
Where is the "off" button on this thing?

1734
01:30:45,760 --> 01:30:46,840
No, no, no, no.

1735
01:30:47,590 --> 01:30:48,720
No...

1736
01:30:54,020 --> 01:30:56,140
No, La Wanda! No means no!

1737
01:31:13,030 --> 01:31:15,490
This is really, really gonna hurt.

1738
01:31:22,040 --> 01:31:24,800
- Bravo, Smurfette! Bravo! - Good job, Smurfette!

1739
01:31:24,880 --> 01:31:26,300
That was amazing!

1740
01:31:26,380 --> 01:31:28,220
Well, that takes care of Gargamel.

1741
01:31:28,630 --> 01:31:30,130
Let's go home, everybody!

1742
01:31:30,220 --> 01:31:31,340
- Yeah! - Home!

1743
01:31:31,430 --> 01:31:33,970
We still have one small problem.

1744
01:31:34,060 --> 01:31:35,810
I've only got five crystals.

1745
01:31:35,970 --> 01:31:39,560
Well, I say no Smurf left behind.

1746
01:31:40,390 --> 01:31:42,690
Wow, Smurfette.

1747
01:31:42,770 --> 01:31:45,230
You are pretty good with that wand.

1748
01:31:45,980 --> 01:31:47,650
It's kind of in my blood.

1749
01:31:47,740 --> 01:31:49,740
Which used to concern me.

1750
01:31:50,400 --> 01:31:52,740
But as someone wonderful once told me,

1751
01:31:52,820 --> 01:31:55,160
it doesn't matter where you came from.

1752
01:31:55,240 --> 01:31:59,080
What matters is who you choose to be.

1753
01:31:59,160 --> 01:32:01,170
That's my girl.

1754
01:32:01,250 --> 01:32:03,420
And you're our papa.

1755
01:32:04,590 --> 01:32:06,500
Thanks for giving us a new home.

1756
01:32:06,590 --> 01:32:08,920
And a new family.

1757
01:32:09,010 --> 01:32:10,550
You're a good Smurf, Papa.

1758
01:32:10,630 --> 01:32:12,930
You'll be a good one, too.

1759
01:32:13,180 --> 01:32:14,600
I'm gonna miss you, Smurfs.

1760
01:32:14,680 --> 01:32:16,220
Maybe you can name a corn dog after them.

1761
01:32:16,470 --> 01:32:18,970
Now you're talking. We could use blue corn.

1762
01:32:19,180 --> 01:32:20,640
Smurf dogs, yum!

1763
01:32:21,270 --> 01:32:22,440
Yes!

1764
01:32:22,520 --> 01:32:23,850
Well, safe travels, guys.

1765
01:32:24,360 --> 01:32:26,360
And smurf back soon.

1766
01:32:26,440 --> 01:32:28,480
Thank you once again, Master Winslow.

1767
01:32:31,400 --> 01:32:32,700
Miss Doolittle.

1768
01:32:33,950 --> 01:32:35,200
Little Blue.

1769
01:32:35,620 --> 01:32:36,950
Papa Vicster.

1770
01:32:38,580 --> 01:32:40,410
- Goodbye, Winslow family. - Goodbye, Papa.

1771
01:32:40,500 --> 01:32:42,160
- Bye-bye! - Toodles!

1772
01:32:42,250 --> 01:32:45,040
- Well, let's go, Smurfs. - Bye-bye, Winslows.

1773
01:32:45,130 --> 01:32:48,670
I can't wait to see the rest of my family.

1774
01:32:51,630 --> 01:32:53,630
Bye, Smurfs!

1775
01:33:04,310 --> 01:33:05,940
- Hey, personal space. - Sorry.

1776
01:33:06,060 --> 01:33:07,400
Papa, you got Smurfette!

1777
01:33:07,770 --> 01:33:09,020
Welcome home, Smurfette!

1778
01:33:09,190 --> 01:33:11,650
- Well, looky here! - Yeah, we're back!

1779
01:33:11,740 --> 01:33:13,570
- Hi, guys! - This is good.

1780
01:33:13,650 --> 01:33:15,820
And some new Smurfs for our family.

1781
01:33:15,910 --> 01:33:17,870
Everyone, this is Vexy.

1782
01:33:17,950 --> 01:33:20,700
- Great goobaloo! - She's a sassy lassie.

1783
01:33:20,790 --> 01:33:21,830
Hi.

1784
01:33:22,000 --> 01:33:23,580
- Hi... - Hi, I'm Greedy.

1785
01:33:23,660 --> 01:33:26,750
Hi, I'm Greedy. You want to share a cupcake?

1786
01:33:30,090 --> 01:33:31,590
- Crikey! - What the hey?

1787
01:33:31,670 --> 01:33:32,880
I nearly smurfed myself.

1788
01:33:33,170 --> 01:33:34,340
Hackus.

1789
01:33:34,430 --> 01:33:36,510
Hackus, these are your new brothers.

1790
01:33:37,010 --> 01:33:38,680
I have new brothers!

1791
01:33:39,010 --> 01:33:40,560
Squeeze!

1792
01:33:40,640 --> 01:33:41,930
Hold on a minute.

1793
01:33:42,020 --> 01:33:43,270
Technically speaking,

1794
01:33:43,350 --> 01:33:46,100
according to section six of the Smurf Code of Genealogical Legitimacy...

1795
01:33:46,190 --> 01:33:47,730
Hey. Just give him a punt.

1796
01:33:47,810 --> 01:33:49,690
- This creature cannot... - Hackus punt!

1797
01:33:50,320 --> 01:33:51,900
- Yeah! - That kid's got style.

1798
01:33:51,980 --> 01:33:53,030
